  "rows": [
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "فعل الكون (am/is/are) يستخدم للحديث عن الهوية والمكان والحالة في الوقت الحاضر. am مع I فقط، is مع المفرد، are مع الجمع",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eThe verb 'to be' (am/is/are)\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eExamples:\u003cbr\u003e• I \u003cb\u003eam\u003c/b\u003e a student.\u003cbr\u003e• She \u003cb\u003eis\u003c/b\u003e at home.\u003cbr\u003e• They \u003cb\u003eare\u003c/b\u003e busy.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use \u003cb\u003eam/is/are\u003c/b\u003e to talk about who we are, where we are, and how we are. This is the present form of the verb 'to be'.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen to use each form:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003eam\u003c/b\u003e with 'I' only\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003eis\u003c/b\u003e with he/she/it and singular nouns\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003eare\u003c/b\u003e with you/we/they and plural nouns",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + am/is/are + complement",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "am",
                "sentence": "I am at work.",
                "translation_ar": "أنا في العمل"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "is",
                "sentence": "My mother is in the kitchen.",
                "translation_ar": "أمي في المطبخ"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "are",
                "sentence": "We are tired after work.",
                "translation_ar": "نحن متعبون بعد العمل"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "is",
                "sentence": "The breakfast is ready.",
                "translation_ar": "الإفطار جاهز"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "are",
                "sentence": "You are early today.",
                "translation_ar": "أنت مبكر اليوم"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I am happy",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم am مع I دائماً، ليس is",
                "wrong": "I is happy"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She is at home",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم is مع المفرد (she/he/it)",
                "wrong": "She are at home"
              },
              {
                "correct": "They are working",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم are مع الجمع (they/we/you)",
                "wrong": "They is working"
              },
              {
                "correct": "My family is big",
                "explanation_ar": "العائلة مفرد في الإنجليزية، استخدم is",
                "wrong": "My family are big"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "d3d043a8-3a16-46e8-bcf8-934ea6c6f481",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Daily Life",
      "topic_name_ar": "am/is/are",
      "topic_name_en": "am/is/are",
      "unit_id": "97ccbf07-a070-4e7f-b27e-4d4a29bcf8d2",
      "unit_number": 1
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "المضارع البسيط يستخدم للعادات والحقائق. مع I, you, we, they نستخدم الفعل الأساسي، ومع he, she, it نضيف -s",
            "content_en": "The \u003cb\u003esimple present\u003c/b\u003e is used to talk about things that happen regularly, habits, and facts.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• I eat rice every day.\u003cbr\u003e• She cooks dinner at 6 PM.\u003cbr\u003e• We drink tea in the morning.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use different forms of the verb depending on who does the action:\u003cbr\u003e• With \u003cb\u003eI, you, we, they\u003c/b\u003e → use the base form of the verb (eat, cook, drink)\u003cbr\u003e• With \u003cb\u003ehe, she, it\u003c/b\u003e → add \u003cb\u003e-s\u003c/b\u003e to the verb (eats, cooks, drinks)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eRemember:\u003c/b\u003e The simple present shows what happens regularly or is always true.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "I/You/We/They + verb + ...\u003cbr\u003eHe/She/It + verb + s + ...",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "cook",
                "sentence": "I cook pasta every Sunday.",
                "translation_ar": "أطبخ المعكرونة كل يوم أحد"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "drinks",
                "sentence": "She drinks coffee in the morning.",
                "translation_ar": "تشرب القهوة في الصباح"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "eat",
                "sentence": "They eat breakfast at 8 AM.",
                "translation_ar": "يتناولون الإفطار في الساعة 8 صباحاً"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "makes",
                "sentence": "He makes pizza on weekends.",
                "translation_ar": "يصنع البيتزا في عطلة نهاية الأسبوع"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "He eats rice.",
                "explanation_ar": "مع he/she/it نضيف -s للفعل",
                "wrong": "He eat rice."
              },
              {
                "correct": "I eat bread.",
                "explanation_ar": "مع I لا نضيف -s للفعل",
                "wrong": "I eats bread."
              },
              {
                "correct": "She cooks soup.",
                "explanation_ar": "مع she يجب إضافة -s",
                "wrong": "She cook soup."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "92cf3884-8f6f-4dfc-a83f-7ffd141ab1b4",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Food \u0026 Cooking",
      "topic_name_ar": "simple present positive",
      "topic_name_en": "simple present positive",
      "unit_id": "a067dbbb-ea5b-4902-938f-ee23952c1c25",
      "unit_number": 2
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "النفي: نضع don't أو doesn't قبل الفعل الأساسي • الأسئلة: نبدأ بـ Do أو Does • الفعل الأساسي يبقى بدون إضافات بعد doesn't و does",
            "content_en": "We use the \u003cb\u003esimple present\u003c/b\u003e to talk about habits, routines, and facts about our city and daily life.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eNegative sentences:\u003c/b\u003e We add \u003ci\u003edon't\u003c/i\u003e (do not) or \u003ci\u003edoesn't\u003c/i\u003e (does not) before the main verb.\u003cbr\u003e• I/You/We/They + \u003cb\u003edon't\u003c/b\u003e + verb\u003cbr\u003e• He/She/It + \u003cb\u003edoesn't\u003c/b\u003e + verb\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eQuestions:\u003c/b\u003e We put \u003ci\u003eDo\u003c/i\u003e or \u003ci\u003eDoes\u003c/i\u003e at the beginning.\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eDo\u003c/b\u003e + I/you/we/they + verb?\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eDoes\u003c/b\u003e + he/she/it + verb?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eRemember: After 'doesn't' and 'does', the main verb stays in base form (no -s).",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Negative: Subject + don't/doesn't + verb | Questions: Do/Does + subject + verb + ?",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "don't live",
                "sentence": "I don't live in the city center.",
                "translation_ar": "أنا لا أعيش في وسط المدينة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "doesn't work",
                "sentence": "She doesn't work in the hospital.",
                "translation_ar": "هي لا تعمل في المستشفى"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Do you like",
                "sentence": "Do you like our city?",
                "translation_ar": "هل تحب مدينتنا؟"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Does he visit",
                "sentence": "Does he visit the museum?",
                "translation_ar": "هل يزور المتحف؟"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "He doesn't work",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نضع -s مع الفعل بعد doesn't",
                "wrong": "He doesn't works"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Does she work?",
                "explanation_ar": "الفعل يبقى أساسي بعد Does",
                "wrong": "Does she works?"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I don't live here",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم don't وليس no للنفي",
                "wrong": "I no live here"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "56cf2f8c-633a-4f4c-8ede-1d40eb8eda0a",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "My City",
      "topic_name_ar": "simple present negative/questions",
      "topic_name_en": "simple present negative/questions",
      "unit_id": "ab2d705a-addc-4aed-9ca2-dc88bce8f448",
      "unit_number": 3
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "هذه الكلمات تستخدم للإشارة إلى الأشياء القريبة والبعيدة. this/that للمفرد، these/those للجمع. this/these للقريب، that/those للبعيد",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eThis/That/These/Those\u003c/b\u003e are words we use to point to things or people.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• This cat is small. (pointing to a cat near me)\u003cbr\u003e• That dog is big. (pointing to a dog far from me)\u003cbr\u003e• These birds are beautiful. (pointing to birds near me)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eThe Rules:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003ethis\u003c/b\u003e for ONE thing NEAR you\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003ethat\u003c/b\u003e for ONE thing FAR from you\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003ethese\u003c/b\u003e for MORE THAN ONE thing NEAR you\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003ethose\u003c/b\u003e for MORE THAN ONE thing FAR from you",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "this/that + singular noun\u003cbr\u003ethese/those + plural noun",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "This rabbit",
                "sentence": "This rabbit is white.",
                "translation_ar": "هذا الأرنب أبيض"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "That elephant",
                "sentence": "That elephant is huge.",
                "translation_ar": "ذلك الفيل ضخم"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "These fish",
                "sentence": "These fish are colorful.",
                "translation_ar": "هذه الأسماك ملونة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Those lions",
                "sentence": "Those lions are strong.",
                "translation_ar": "تلك الأسود قوية"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "These cats are small",
                "explanation_ar": "this للمفرد فقط، استخدم these للجمع",
                "wrong": "This cats are small"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Those birds are flying",
                "explanation_ar": "that للمفرد فقط، استخدم those للجمع",
                "wrong": "That birds are flying"
              },
              {
                "correct": "This dog is cute",
                "explanation_ar": "these للجمع فقط، استخدم this للمفرد",
                "wrong": "These dog is cute"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "e82ff626-9e18-4316-bfa0-cc8431177fad",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Animals Around Us",
      "topic_name_ar": "this/that/these/those",
      "topic_name_en": "this/that/these/those",
      "unit_id": "a1c18caa-29d6-4ae7-9ed4-9ca2702f6af4",
      "unit_number": 4
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "في الإنجليزية نضيف -s أو -es للأسماء للجمع • معظم الأسماء نضيف لها -s • الأسماء المنتهية بـ s, x, ch, sh نضيف لها -es • بعض الأسماء شاذة",
            "content_en": "In English, we add \u003cb\u003e-s\u003c/b\u003e or \u003cb\u003e-es\u003c/b\u003e to nouns to make them plural (more than one).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• One \u003cb\u003eseason\u003c/b\u003e → Four \u003cb\u003eseasons\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• One \u003cb\u003ecloud\u003c/b\u003e → Many \u003cb\u003eclouds\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• One \u003cb\u003erainy day\u003c/b\u003e → Two \u003cb\u003erainy days\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eRules:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. Most nouns: add \u003cb\u003e-s\u003c/b\u003e (cloud → clouds, tree → trees)\u003cbr\u003e2. Nouns ending in -s, -x, -ch, -sh: add \u003cb\u003e-es\u003c/b\u003e (box → boxes)\u003cbr\u003e3. Some nouns are irregular (child → children, leaf → leaves)",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Singular noun + -s/-es = Plural noun",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "days",
                "sentence": "Winter has cold days.",
                "translation_ar": "الشتاء له أيام باردة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "clouds",
                "sentence": "I see many clouds in the sky.",
                "translation_ar": "أرى غيوماً كثيرة في السماء"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "flowers, leaves",
                "sentence": "Spring brings flowers and leaves.",
                "translation_ar": "الربيع يجلب الزهور والأوراق"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "two days",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنسَ إضافة -s للجمع",
                "wrong": "two day"
              },
              {
                "correct": "many clouds",
                "explanation_ar": "مع many نستخدم الجمع دائماً",
                "wrong": "many cloud"
              },
              {
                "correct": "leaves",
                "explanation_ar": "leaf كلمة شاذة في الجمع",
                "wrong": "leafs"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "1de0dca0-34b3-4c4a-b527-dc55cf08926f",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Weather \u0026 Seasons",
      "topic_name_ar": "plurals",
      "topic_name_en": "plurals",
      "unit_id": "ffa3641f-b0c8-412b-a5ab-dc60603018ea",
      "unit_number": 5
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "أدوات التعريف والتنكير في الإنجليزية مختلفة عن العربية. استخدم a/an للأشياء غير المحددة، و the للأشياء المحددة أو المعروفة",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eArticles\u003c/b\u003e are small words we use before nouns.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eA/An\u003c/b\u003e = one thing (not specific)\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003e'a'\u003c/b\u003e before consonant sounds: \u003ci\u003ea friend, a sister\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003e'an'\u003c/b\u003e before vowel sounds: \u003ci\u003ean uncle, an old friend\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eThe\u003c/b\u003e = specific thing (we know which one)\u003cbr\u003e• Use when we know exactly which person/thing: \u003ci\u003ethe father, the family\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Use when there is only one: \u003ci\u003ethe mother (in a family)\u003c/i\u003e",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "a/an + singular noun (indefinite) | the + noun (definite)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "a brother",
                "sentence": "I have a brother.",
                "translation_ar": "لدي أخ"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "an aunt",
                "sentence": "She is an aunt.",
                "translation_ar": "هي عمة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "The mother",
                "sentence": "The mother is cooking.",
                "translation_ar": "الأم تطبخ"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "a friend",
                "sentence": "I want to meet a friend.",
                "translation_ar": "أريد أن ألتقي بصديق"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "The family",
                "sentence": "The family is happy.",
                "translation_ar": "الأسرة سعيدة"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I have a brother",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس أداة التنكير قبل الاسم المفرد",
                "wrong": "I have brother"
              },
              {
                "correct": "an uncle",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم 'an' قبل الأصوات المتحركة",
                "wrong": "a uncle"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I like the mother",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم 'the' عندما تتحدث عن شخص محدد ومعروف",
                "wrong": "I like a mother"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "4fd72f99-b0ee-40fd-8220-2c7075c15cd5",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Family \u0026 Friends",
      "topic_name_ar": "a/an/the basics",
      "topic_name_en": "a/an/the basics",
      "unit_id": "0afc0986-f79d-426c-bb15-ee66dd77e5d9",
      "unit_number": 6
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم there is/there are للتعبير عن وجود شيء في مكان معين • there is للمفرد • there are للجمع • مفيدة لوصف ما موجود في المحلات والأسواق",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eThere is/There are\u003c/b\u003e tells us that something exists in a place.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• There is a bank on this street.\u003cbr\u003e• There are many shops in the mall.\u003cbr\u003e• There is money in my wallet.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen to use:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003ethere is\u003c/b\u003e with \u003ci\u003eone thing\u003c/i\u003e (singular)\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003ethere are\u003c/b\u003e with \u003ci\u003emore than one thing\u003c/i\u003e (plural)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWe often use it to describe:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• What we can see in shops, markets, or stores\u003cbr\u003e• What exists in different places\u003cbr\u003e• What is available to buy",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "There is + singular noun + place\u003cbr\u003eThere are + plural noun + place",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "There is",
                "sentence": "There is a supermarket near my house.",
                "translation_ar": "يوجد سوبر ماركت قريب من بيتي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "There are",
                "sentence": "There are three banks in this area.",
                "translation_ar": "يوجد ثلاثة بنوك في هذه المنطقة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "There is",
                "sentence": "There is some change in my pocket.",
                "translation_ar": "يوجد بعض الفكة في جيبي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "There are",
                "sentence": "There are expensive clothes in that shop.",
                "translation_ar": "يوجد ملابس غالية في ذلك المحل"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "There is a shop",
                "explanation_ar": "a shop مفرد، لذلك نستخدم there is",
                "wrong": "There are a shop"
              },
              {
                "correct": "There are many stores",
                "explanation_ar": "many stores جمع، لذلك نستخدم there are",
                "wrong": "There is many stores"
              },
              {
                "correct": "There is a bank",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم have مع there، نستخدم is أو are",
                "wrong": "There have a bank"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "8a3e9f5f-9b9f-4df5-87af-94c7071596b7",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Shopping \u0026 Money",
      "topic_name_ar": "there is/there are",
      "topic_name_en": "there is/there are",
      "unit_id": "5515ee31-f957-4daa-bdde-4cffda7704c7",
      "unit_number": 7
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم 's للملكية مع الأشخاص فقط. نضيف 's بعد اسم الشخص مباشرة، ثم الشيء المملوك. مثل: كتاب أحمد = Ahmed's book",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePossessive 's\u003c/b\u003e shows that something belongs to someone.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• The doctor's coat is white.\u003cbr\u003e• Sara's arm is broken.\u003cbr\u003e• My mother's head hurts.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eHow to use it:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe add \u003cb\u003e's\u003c/b\u003e to a person's name or noun to show they own something. The possessive 's comes \u003cb\u003ebefore\u003c/b\u003e the thing they own.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eImportant:\u003c/b\u003e We use possessive 's with people, not things. We say 'the doctor's bag' but 'the door of the hospital' (not 'the hospital's door').",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Person's name + 's + thing owned",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "nurse's",
                "sentence": "The nurse's hands are clean.",
                "translation_ar": "يدا الممرضة نظيفتان"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Ahmed's",
                "sentence": "Ahmed's tooth hurts.",
                "translation_ar": "سن أحمد يؤلمه"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "baby's",
                "sentence": "The baby's eyes are blue.",
                "translation_ar": "عينا الطفل زرقاوان"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "The doctor's coat",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس إضافة الفاصلة العليا والـ s",
                "wrong": "The doctors coat"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The door of the hospital",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم 's مع الأشياء، فقط مع الأشخاص",
                "wrong": "The hospital's door"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Sara's head",
                "explanation_ar": "يجب إضافة s بعد الفاصلة العليا",
                "wrong": "Sara' head"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "7405ab5f-3afb-4b04-8035-4abb3b4554b0",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Health \u0026 Body",
      "topic_name_ar": "possessive s",
      "topic_name_en": "possessive s",
      "unit_id": "bae5cc8f-ae31-4688-93fb-e2cd73406804",
      "unit_number": 8
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الضمائر في الإنجليزية لها أشكال مختلفة: I للفاعل، me للمفعول به، my للملكية",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePronouns I, me, my\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use different pronouns for different positions in sentences:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eI\u003c/b\u003e = subject (does the action)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eme\u003c/b\u003e = object (receives the action)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003emy\u003c/b\u003e = possessive (shows ownership)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThink of it like this:\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eI\u003c/b\u003e comes before the verb\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eme\u003c/b\u003e comes after verbs or prepositions (to, for, with)\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003emy\u003c/b\u003e comes before nouns to show 'this belongs to me'",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "I + verb | verb + me | my + noun",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "I",
                "sentence": "I love reading books.",
                "translation_ar": "أحب قراءة الكتب"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "me",
                "sentence": "Music helps me relax.",
                "translation_ar": "الموسيقى تساعدني على الاسترخاء"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "My",
                "sentence": "My hobby is painting.",
                "translation_ar": "هوايتي هي الرسم"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I like swimming",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم I مع الفعل كفاعل وليس me",
                "wrong": "Me like swimming"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Give the ball to me",
                "explanation_ar": "بعد حروف الجر نستخدم me وليس I",
                "wrong": "Give the ball to I"
              },
              {
                "correct": "This is my guitar",
                "explanation_ar": "للملكية نستخدم my وليس I",
                "wrong": "This is I guitar"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "98e7f011-e467-43aa-bf09-3c707fa0d0df",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Hobbies \u0026 Free Time",
      "topic_name_ar": "pronouns (I/me/my)",
      "topic_name_en": "pronouns (I/me/my)",
      "unit_id": "89f2e975-060e-4f83-a4bf-b2c86ec56631",
      "unit_number": 9
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الأمر يستخدم لإعطاء الأوامر والتعليمات. في السفر، ستسمع الكثير من الأوامر في المطار والفندق",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eImperatives\u003c/b\u003e are used to give commands, instructions, or requests.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eTake\u003c/i\u003e your passport.\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eShow\u003c/i\u003e your ticket.\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eDon't forget\u003c/i\u003e your luggage.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use imperatives when we tell someone what to do. In travel situations, you will hear many imperatives from airport staff, hotel workers, and tour guides.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003ePositive imperatives:\u003c/b\u003e We use the base form of the verb (infinitive without 'to').\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eNegative imperatives:\u003c/b\u003e We add 'Don't' before the verb.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Positive: Verb + object | Negative: Don't + verb + object",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "Check",
                "sentence": "Check your boarding pass.",
                "translation_ar": "تحقق من بطاقة الصعود"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Don't lose",
                "sentence": "Don't lose your passport.",
                "translation_ar": "لا تفقد جواز سفرك"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Follow",
                "sentence": "Follow the signs to Gate 5.",
                "translation_ar": "اتبع اللافتات إلى البوابة 5"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Check your ticket.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم الضمير في الأمر",
                "wrong": "You check your ticket."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Don't lose your passport.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم Don't وليس No في النفي",
                "wrong": "No lose your passport."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Show your ID.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم to مع الأمر",
                "wrong": "To show your ID."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "77003126-4fd3-4066-b5f4-56f4dd1015a2",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Travel Basics",
      "topic_name_ar": "imperatives",
      "topic_name_en": "imperatives",
      "unit_id": "a543f5ca-e28d-4c52-90d1-f2027af29da2",
      "unit_number": 10
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "ترتيب الصفات في الإنجليزية مهم. الحجم يأتي قبل اللون. مثال: هاتف أسود صغير = small black phone",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eAdjective Order Basics\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLook at these sentences:\u003cbr\u003e• I have a \u003cb\u003enew small\u003c/b\u003e phone.\u003cbr\u003e• She bought a \u003cb\u003ebig black\u003c/b\u003e laptop.\u003cbr\u003e• This is an \u003cb\u003eold expensive\u003c/b\u003e tablet.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIn English, when we use two adjectives together, we put them in a special order:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eSize + Age + Color + Noun\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eor\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eOpinion + Size + Age + Color + Noun\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFor beginners, remember: \u003cb\u003eSize comes before Color\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eExamples: small black phone, big white computer, tiny red camera\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe usually don't use more than 2-3 adjectives together at this level.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Size + Color + Noun OR Opinion + Size + Color + Noun",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "small black",
                "sentence": "I want a small black smartphone.",
                "translation_ar": "أريد هاتفاً ذكياً أسود صغير"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "big white",
                "sentence": "He has a big white computer.",
                "translation_ar": "لديه حاسوب أبيض كبير"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "nice small",
                "sentence": "This is a nice small tablet.",
                "translation_ar": "هذا جهاز لوحي صغير جميل"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "expensive new",
                "sentence": "She bought an expensive new laptop.",
                "translation_ar": "اشترت حاسوباً محمولاً جديداً غالياً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "small black phone",
                "explanation_ar": "الحجم يأتي قبل اللون دائماً",
                "wrong": "black small phone"
              },
              {
                "correct": "big red camera",
                "explanation_ar": "كبير يأتي قبل أحمر",
                "wrong": "red big camera"
              },
              {
                "correct": "nice old tablet",
                "explanation_ar": "الرأي (جميل) يأتي قبل العمر (قديم)",
                "wrong": "old nice tablet"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "20329999-1122-482b-9529-ef0ddcf355b0",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Technology Today",
      "topic_name_ar": "adjective order basics",
      "topic_name_en": "adjective order basics",
      "unit_id": "8fa91a36-703f-46ae-a893-e5162de9bf2d",
      "unit_number": 11
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "حروف الجر للمكان تخبرنا أين يقع الشيء أو الشخص. نستخدمها لوصف موقع الأشياء والأشخاص بالنسبة لأشياء أخرى",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePrepositions of place\u003c/b\u003e tell us \u003ci\u003ewhere\u003c/i\u003e something or someone is.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use prepositions of place to describe the location of people and things in relation to other objects.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe most common prepositions of place are:\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003ein\u003c/b\u003e - inside something\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eon\u003c/b\u003e - on top of something\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eat\u003c/b\u003e - at a specific place/location\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eunder\u003c/b\u003e - below something\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003ebehind\u003c/b\u003e - at the back of something\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003ein front of\u003c/b\u003e - before something\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003enext to\u003c/b\u003e - beside something\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003ebetween\u003c/b\u003e - in the middle of two things",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + be verb + preposition of place + object/location",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "in",
                "sentence": "The doctor is in the hospital.",
                "translation_ar": "الطبيب في المستشفى"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "in front of",
                "sentence": "The teacher stands in front of the class.",
                "translation_ar": "المعلم يقف أمام الصف"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "at",
                "sentence": "The chef works at the restaurant.",
                "translation_ar": "الطاهي يعمل في المطعم"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "The nurse is in the hospital room.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم in للأماكن المغلقة وليس at",
                "wrong": "The nurse is at the hospital room."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The books are on the table.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم on للأسطح وليس in",
                "wrong": "The books are in the table."
              },
              {
                "correct": "He works at McDonald's.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم at مع أسماء المحلات والشركات المحددة",
                "wrong": "He works in McDonald's."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "ee6732f0-c24a-444b-b42f-df96da9b1de2",
      "level_id": "cd96175e-76d4-48dc-b34f-83f3228a28b8",
      "level_number": 0,
      "theme_en": "Jobs \u0026 Careers",
      "topic_name_ar": "prepositions of place",
      "topic_name_en": "prepositions of place",
      "unit_id": "2f3df52f-08c0-4fd0-9488-487ddd956140",
      "unit_number": 12
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الماضي البسيط للأفعال المنتظمة: نضيف -ed للفعل الأساسي للتعبير عن أحداث انتهت في الماضي",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eSimple Past Tense - Regular Verbs\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use the simple past tense to talk about actions that happened and finished in the past.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eHow to form regular past tense:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eAdd \u003cb\u003e-ed\u003c/b\u003e to the base form of regular verbs.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eSpelling rules:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Most verbs: add -ed (walk → walked)\u003cbr\u003e• Verbs ending in -e: add -d (dance → danced)\u003cbr\u003e• Verbs ending in consonant + y: change y to i + ed (study → studied)\u003cbr\u003e• Short verbs ending in consonant-vowel-consonant: double the last consonant + ed (stop → stopped)",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + Verb + ed",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "celebrated",
                "sentence": "We celebrated Eid with our family last month.",
                "translation_ar": "احتفلنا بالعيد مع عائلتنا الشهر الماضي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "danced",
                "sentence": "She danced at the wedding festival yesterday.",
                "translation_ar": "رقصت في حفل الزفاف أمس"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "watched",
                "sentence": "They watched the parade during the national holiday.",
                "translation_ar": "شاهدوا المسيرة خلال العطلة الوطنية"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I celebrated Eid yesterday",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس إضافة -ed للماضي",
                "wrong": "I celebrate Eid yesterday"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She danced at the party",
                "explanation_ar": "الأفعال المنتهية بـ e نضيف فقط d",
                "wrong": "She danceed at the party"
              },
              {
                "correct": "We studied about festivals",
                "explanation_ar": "الأفعال المنتهية بـ y نحولها إلى ied",
                "wrong": "We studyed about festivals"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "91c091d2-c56d-4ceb-86c2-164a1dc9a2ae",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Cultural Festivals",
      "topic_name_ar": "simple past (regular)",
      "topic_name_en": "simple past (regular)",
      "unit_id": "49ed7c2c-fa1b-47b2-bb5c-34074beeafdc",
      "unit_number": 1
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الأفعال الشاذة في الماضي البسيط لا تأخذ ed- بل تتغير تماماً • يجب حفظ هذه الأشكال • تستخدم مع جميع الضمائر بنفس الشكل",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eSimple Past - Irregular Verbs\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• The whale \u003cb\u003eswam\u003c/b\u003e in the deep ocean.\u003cbr\u003e• We \u003cb\u003esaw\u003c/b\u003e colorful fish yesterday.\u003cbr\u003e• The dolphin \u003cb\u003ewent\u003c/b\u003e under the water.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhat are irregular verbs?\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eMost verbs add '-ed' for past tense (regular verbs), but irregular verbs change completely. We must memorize these forms.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eCommon irregular verbs in ocean context:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• see → saw (I saw a shark)\u003cbr\u003e• swim → swam (The fish swam away)\u003cbr\u003e• go → went (We went diving)\u003cbr\u003e• come → came (The turtle came to the surface)\u003cbr\u003e• find → found (They found shells on the beach)\u003cbr\u003e• eat → ate (The whale ate krill)\u003cbr\u003e• get → got (We got wet in the sea)\u003cbr\u003e• have → had (The octopus had eight arms)",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + irregular past form + rest of sentence",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "swam",
                "sentence": "The shark swam near the boat.",
                "translation_ar": "سبح القرش بالقرب من القارب"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "saw",
                "sentence": "We saw many dolphins yesterday.",
                "translation_ar": "رأينا العديد من الدلافين أمس"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "went",
                "sentence": "The crab went into its shell.",
                "translation_ar": "دخل السرطان إلى قوقعته"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I saw a whale",
                "explanation_ar": "see في الماضي تصبح saw وليس seed",
                "wrong": "I seed a whale"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The fish swam",
                "explanation_ar": "swim شاذ، في الماضي swam وليس swimmed",
                "wrong": "The fish swimmed"
              },
              {
                "correct": "We went to the beach",
                "explanation_ar": "go في الماضي went وليس goed",
                "wrong": "We goed to the beach"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "ddf64e5e-ce1c-4126-a034-a89b635f0670",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Ocean Life",
      "topic_name_ar": "simple past (irregular)",
      "topic_name_en": "simple past (irregular)",
      "unit_id": "1de8e161-81eb-416e-af87-c136d93f3930",
      "unit_number": 2
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "النفي: didn't + الفعل في شكله الأساسي\u003cbr\u003eالسؤال: Did + الفاعل + الفعل في شكله الأساسي\u003cbr\u003eمهم: بعد did أو didn't نستخدم الفعل في شكله الأساسي وليس الماضي",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePast Simple Negative and Questions\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLook at these examples:\u003cbr\u003e• The rocket \u003cb\u003edid not land\u003c/b\u003e on Mars yesterday.\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eDid\u003c/b\u003e the astronaut \u003cb\u003ewalk\u003c/b\u003e on the moon?\u003cbr\u003e• We \u003cb\u003edidn't see\u003c/b\u003e any stars last night.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eHow to make Past Simple negative:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eUse 'did not' (didn't) + base form of the verb\u003cbr\u003eExample: The satellite didn't work properly.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eHow to make Past Simple questions:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eUse 'Did' + subject + base form of the verb + ?\u003cbr\u003eExample: Did NASA launch the rocket?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eImportant:\u003c/b\u003e After 'did' and 'didn't', always use the base form of the verb (not past tense).",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Negative: Subject + didn't + base verb\u003cbr\u003eQuestion: Did + subject + base verb + ?",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "didn't return",
                "sentence": "The astronauts didn't return to Earth yesterday.",
                "translation_ar": "لم يعد رواد الفضاء إلى الأرض أمس"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Did you watch",
                "sentence": "Did you watch the rocket launch?",
                "translation_ar": "هل شاهدت إطلاق الصاروخ؟"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "didn't reach",
                "sentence": "The spaceship didn't reach the moon.",
                "translation_ar": "لم تصل المركبة الفضائية إلى القمر"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "He didn't go to the space center.",
                "explanation_ar": "بعد didn't نستخدم الفعل الأساسي وليس الماضي",
                "wrong": "He didn't went to the space center."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Did he go to see the rocket?",
                "explanation_ar": "بعد Did نستخدم الفعل الأساسي",
                "wrong": "Did he went to see the rocket?"
              },
              {
                "correct": "They didn't visit the space museum.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم didn't وليس no للنفي في الماضي",
                "wrong": "They no visited the space museum."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "8508eae7-120f-4408-ae5d-4f76172c9040",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Space Exploration",
      "topic_name_ar": "past negative/questions",
      "topic_name_en": "past negative/questions",
      "unit_id": "dfefdb76-330a-4ac3-9102-95e1b792a5a6",
      "unit_number": 3
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم المضارع المستمر للحديث عن الأعمال التي تحدث الآن أو في هذه اللحظة. الفعل بدأ قبل الآن وسيستمر بعد الآن.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePresent Continuous Tense\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use the present continuous to talk about actions happening \u003cb\u003eright now\u003c/b\u003e or \u003cb\u003eat this moment\u003c/b\u003e.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• She is playing the piano now.\u003cbr\u003e• The children are drawing pictures.\u003cbr\u003e• I am listening to music at the moment.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe present continuous shows that an action is \u003cb\u003ein progress\u003c/b\u003e - it started before now and will continue after now.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eTime words we often use:\u003c/b\u003e now, right now, at the moment, currently, today",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + am/is/are + verb-ing",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "is singing",
                "sentence": "She is singing a beautiful song.",
                "translation_ar": "إنها تغني أغنية جميلة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "is painting",
                "sentence": "The artist is painting a portrait now.",
                "translation_ar": "الفنان يرسم بورتريه الآن"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "are watching",
                "sentence": "We are watching a concert today.",
                "translation_ar": "نحن نشاهد حفلة موسيقية اليوم"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "am learning",
                "sentence": "I am learning to play guitar.",
                "translation_ar": "أنا أتعلم العزف على الجيتار"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "He is playing piano now",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس فعل الكون (am/is/are)",
                "wrong": "He playing piano now"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I am playing music",
                "explanation_ar": "أضف -ing للفعل الأساسي",
                "wrong": "I am play music"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She is drawing",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم 'is' مع she/he/it",
                "wrong": "She are drawing"
              },
              {
                "correct": "They are dancing",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم 'are' مع they/we/you",
                "wrong": "They is dancing"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "9395672e-dc1f-4d45-941d-65a852c3974d",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Music \u0026 Art",
      "topic_name_ar": "present continuous",
      "topic_name_en": "present continuous",
      "unit_id": "95530744-5815-4ca5-bb10-756b25cc66d6",
      "unit_number": 4
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "can للقدرة والإمكانية، can't للعدم القدرة. نفس الشكل لجميع الضمائر",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eCan/Can't\u003c/b\u003e are used to talk about ability and possibility.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• I \u003cb\u003ecan\u003c/b\u003e visit the Eiffel Tower next week.\u003cbr\u003e• She \u003cb\u003ecan't\u003c/b\u003e see the Pyramids from here.\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eCan\u003c/b\u003e you climb Mount Everest?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eUse:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eCan\u003c/b\u003e = able to do something, possible\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eCan't\u003c/b\u003e = not able to do something, not possible\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eCan/Can't\u003c/b\u003e is the same for all persons (I, you, he, she, it, we, they).",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + can/can't + base verb (infinitive without 'to')",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "can see",
                "sentence": "I can see Big Ben from the bridge.",
                "translation_ar": "يمكنني رؤية بيغ بن من الجسر"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "can't visit",
                "sentence": "We can't visit the Great Wall today.",
                "translation_ar": "لا يمكننا زيارة سور الصين العظيم اليوم"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Can tourists enter",
                "sentence": "Can tourists enter the Colosseum?",
                "translation_ar": "هل يمكن للسياح دخول الكولوسيوم؟"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I can visit",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم 'to' بعد can",
                "wrong": "I can to visit"
              },
              {
                "correct": "He can speak",
                "explanation_ar": "can لا تتغير مع الضمائر، لا نضيف s",
                "wrong": "He cans speak"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I can't go",
                "explanation_ar": "النفي بـ can't وليس not can",
                "wrong": "I not can go"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "279395e2-009d-40c5-91df-cd4f501c48f3",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Famous Places",
      "topic_name_ar": "can/cant",
      "topic_name_en": "can/cant",
      "unit_id": "9a560631-9d0b-4b5a-a3d5-567c1779ab6e",
      "unit_number": 5
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الأسماء المعدودة يمكن عدها (واحد، اثنان، ثلاثة) والأسماء غير المعدودة لا يمكن عدها. الأسماء المعدودة لها مفرد وجمع، أما غير المعدودة فليس لها صيغة جمع.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eCountable and Uncountable Nouns\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSome nouns we can count (1, 2, 3...) and some we cannot count.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eCountable nouns:\u003c/b\u003e We can count them. They have singular and plural forms.\u003cbr\u003eExamples: one computer → two computers, one phone → three phones\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eUncountable nouns:\u003c/b\u003e We cannot count them. They don't have plural forms.\u003cbr\u003eExamples: water, electricity, plastic, information\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWith countable nouns we use: \u003ci\u003ea/an, many, few, number\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWith uncountable nouns we use: \u003ci\u003emuch, little, some, a lot of\u003c/i\u003e",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Countable: a/an + singular noun, many/few + plural noun\u003cbr\u003eUncountable: much/little/some + noun (no plural)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "telephone",
                "sentence": "The telephone is a useful invention.",
                "translation_ar": "الهاتف اختراع مفيد"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Electricity",
                "sentence": "Electricity changed the world.",
                "translation_ar": "الكهرباء غيرت العالم"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "many computers",
                "sentence": "We have many computers in the office.",
                "translation_ar": "لدينا حاسوبات كثيرة في المكتب"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I need much electricity",
                "explanation_ar": "electricity غير معدودة، نستخدم much وليس many",
                "wrong": "I need many electricity"
              },
              {
                "correct": "He has some information",
                "explanation_ar": "information غير معدودة، لا تأخذ s ولا نستخدم معها أرقام",
                "wrong": "He has three informations"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I bought many phones",
                "explanation_ar": "phones معدودة، نستخدم many وليس much",
                "wrong": "I bought much phones"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "c23e3c76-669e-4201-bfad-88dbe5af3bf5",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Inventions",
      "topic_name_ar": "countable/uncountable",
      "topic_name_en": "countable/uncountable",
      "unit_id": "55a4d6c2-9130-40db-983d-ed412ba446a7",
      "unit_number": 6
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم some في الجمل الإيجابية، و any في الجمل السلبية والأسئلة. Some تعني 'بعض' أو 'قليل'، بينما any تُستخدم عندما لا نعرف الكمية أو عندما لا يوجد شيء.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eSome/Any\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Cristiano Ronaldo has \u003cb\u003esome\u003c/b\u003e trophies in his room.\u003cbr\u003e• Does Messi have \u003cb\u003eany\u003c/b\u003e free time?\u003cbr\u003e• The team doesn't have \u003cb\u003eany\u003c/b\u003e new players.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eRules:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use \u003cb\u003esome\u003c/b\u003e in positive sentences (+)\u003cbr\u003eWe use \u003cb\u003eany\u003c/b\u003e in negative sentences (-) and questions (?)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eSome\u003c/b\u003e = a little bit, a few (but not zero)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eAny\u003c/b\u003e = used when we don't know the amount or there is zero",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Positive: Subject + verb + some + noun\u003cbr\u003eNegative: Subject + don't/doesn't + verb + any + noun\u003cbr\u003eQuestion: Do/Does + subject + verb + any + noun?",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "some",
                "sentence": "Serena Williams has some tennis rackets.",
                "translation_ar": "سيرينا ويليامز لديها بعض مضارب التنس"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "any",
                "sentence": "The football player doesn't have any injuries.",
                "translation_ar": "لاعب كرة القدم ليس لديه أي إصابات"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "any",
                "sentence": "Do you have any favorite basketball players?",
                "translation_ar": "هل لديك أي لاعبي كرة سلة مفضلين؟"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Do you have any money?",
                "explanation_ar": "في الأسئلة نستخدم any وليس some",
                "wrong": "Do you have some money?"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I don't have any time.",
                "explanation_ar": "في الجمل السلبية نستخدم any وليس some",
                "wrong": "I don't have some time."
              },
              {
                "correct": "He has some trophies.",
                "explanation_ar": "في الجمل الإيجابية نستخدم some وليس any",
                "wrong": "He has any trophies."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "78740d3d-c0b5-4449-893c-167c6799e15a",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Sports Stars",
      "topic_name_ar": "some/any",
      "topic_name_en": "some/any",
      "unit_id": "f3a651e1-3ae8-4028-a5fa-42e44f5af75b",
      "unit_number": 7
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم How many مع الأسماء القابلة للعد، و How much مع الأسماء غير القابلة للعد",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eHow Much\u003c/b\u003e and \u003cb\u003eHow Many\u003c/b\u003e are used to ask about quantity.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• How many pyramids are in Egypt? - There are many pyramids in Egypt.\u003cbr\u003e• How much gold did the pharaohs have? - They had a lot of gold.\u003cbr\u003e• How many people lived in ancient Rome? - Millions of people lived there.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eThe Rule:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eUse \u003cb\u003eHOW MANY\u003c/b\u003e with countable nouns (things you can count: 1, 2, 3...)\u003cbr\u003eUse \u003cb\u003eHOW MUCH\u003c/b\u003e with uncountable nouns (things you cannot count individually)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eCountable:\u003c/b\u003e pyramids, temples, soldiers, kings\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eUncountable:\u003c/b\u003e gold, water, food, time, money",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "How many + countable noun + ?\u003cbr\u003eHow much + uncountable noun + ?",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "How many temples",
                "sentence": "How many temples did the Romans build?",
                "translation_ar": "كم معبداً بنى الرومان؟"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "How much silver",
                "sentence": "How much silver was used in ancient coins?",
                "translation_ar": "كم من الفضة استُخدمت في النقود القديمة؟"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "How many gods",
                "sentence": "How many gods did the Egyptians worship?",
                "translation_ar": "كم إلهاً عبد المصريون؟"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "How many pyramids are there?",
                "explanation_ar": "الأهرامات قابلة للعد، لذا نستخدم How many",
                "wrong": "How much pyramids are there?"
              },
              {
                "correct": "How much gold did they find?",
                "explanation_ar": "الذهب غير قابل للعد، لذا نستخدم How much",
                "wrong": "How many gold did they find?"
              },
              {
                "correct": "How many soldiers were there?",
                "explanation_ar": "الجنود قابلون للعد، لذا نستخدم How many",
                "wrong": "How much soldiers were there?"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "a35236a4-ee1e-4217-aa65-76faf4c99c46",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Ancient Civilizations",
      "topic_name_ar": "how much/how many",
      "topic_name_en": "how much/how many",
      "unit_id": "34f36fbb-3cc6-4f5f-be54-491491297386",
      "unit_number": 8
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "حروف الجر الزمنية: in للشهور والسنوات والفصول وأجزاء اليوم، on للأيام والتواريخ، at للأوقات المحددة",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePrepositions of Time: in, on, at\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use prepositions of time to say WHEN something happens.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eIN\u003c/b\u003e - for months, years, seasons, and parts of the day\u003cbr\u003e• I take photos \u003cb\u003ein\u003c/b\u003e summer.\u003cbr\u003e• She bought a camera \u003cb\u003ein\u003c/b\u003e 2023.\u003cbr\u003e• We edit photos \u003cb\u003ein\u003c/b\u003e the morning.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eON\u003c/b\u003e - for days and dates\u003cbr\u003e• The photography class is \u003cb\u003eon\u003c/b\u003e Monday.\u003cbr\u003e• I took this picture \u003cb\u003eon\u003c/b\u003e June 15th.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eAT\u003c/b\u003e - for specific times\u003cbr\u003e• The photo exhibition opens \u003cb\u003eat\u003c/b\u003e 6 PM.\u003cbr\u003e• I wake up \u003cb\u003eat\u003c/b\u003e 7:00 to catch sunrise photos.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + verb + preposition (in/on/at) + time expression",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "in spring",
                "sentence": "I take beautiful photos in spring.",
                "translation_ar": "ألتقط صوراً جميلة في الربيع"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "on Sunday",
                "sentence": "The camera shop closes on Sunday.",
                "translation_ar": "متجر الكاميرات مغلق يوم الأحد"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "at 2 PM",
                "sentence": "We start the photography workshop at 2 PM.",
                "translation_ar": "نبدأ ورشة التصوير في الساعة الثانية مساءً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "on Monday",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم on مع الأيام وليس at",
                "wrong": "at Monday"
              },
              {
                "correct": "at 3 o'clock",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم at مع الساعات المحددة",
                "wrong": "on 3 o'clock"
              },
              {
                "correct": "at night",
                "explanation_ar": "at night تعبير ثابت، نقول at night وليس in night",
                "wrong": "in night"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "eee808c4-4aa2-4f76-987e-de2bb0a062f9",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Photography",
      "topic_name_ar": "prepositions of time",
      "topic_name_en": "prepositions of time",
      "unit_id": "357a1833-dd03-4232-8218-19d5d297edd8",
      "unit_number": 9
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "ظروف التكرار تخبرنا عن مدى تكرار الحدث. تأتي قبل الفعل الأساسي وبعد فعل الكون (am/is/are)",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eAdverbs of frequency\u003c/b\u003e tell us how often something happens.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• I \u003cb\u003ealways\u003c/b\u003e eat Italian pasta for dinner.\u003cbr\u003e• She \u003cb\u003esometimes\u003c/b\u003e cooks Chinese food.\u003cbr\u003e• We \u003cb\u003enever\u003c/b\u003e try spicy Indian curry.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eCommon adverbs of frequency (from most to least frequent):\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003ealways\u003c/b\u003e (100%) - دائماً\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eusually\u003c/b\u003e (90%) - عادة\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eoften\u003c/b\u003e (70%) - غالباً\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003esometimes\u003c/b\u003e (50%) - أحياناً\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003erarely/seldom\u003c/b\u003e (10%) - نادراً\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003enever\u003c/b\u003e (0%) - أبداً\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003ePosition:\u003c/b\u003e Adverbs of frequency come \u003cb\u003ebefore the main verb\u003c/b\u003e but \u003cb\u003eafter the verb 'be'\u003c/b\u003e.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + adverb of frequency + main verb OR Subject + be + adverb of frequency",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "always",
                "sentence": "I always eat rice with my meals.",
                "translation_ar": "أنا دائماً آكل الأرز مع وجباتي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "usually",
                "sentence": "He usually orders pizza on weekends.",
                "translation_ar": "هو عادة يطلب البيتزا في نهاية الأسبوع"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "sometimes",
                "sentence": "They are sometimes hungry for Mexican food.",
                "translation_ar": "هم أحياناً جائعون للطعام المكسيكي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "never",
                "sentence": "We never cook Thai food at home.",
                "translation_ar": "نحن لا نطبخ الطعام التايلاندي في البيت أبداً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I always eat pasta.",
                "explanation_ar": "ظرف التكرار يأتي قبل الفعل الأساسي وليس بعده",
                "wrong": "I eat always pasta."
              },
              {
                "correct": "She never cooks Chinese food.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم فعل الكون مع الفعل الأساسي",
                "wrong": "She is never cook Chinese food."
              },
              {
                "correct": "They are sometimes hungry.",
                "explanation_ar": "مع فعل الكون، ظرف التكرار يأتي بعد الفعل",
                "wrong": "They sometimes are hungry."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "be55daa7-4be4-47c3-80c0-4e7a19930dab",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "World Cuisines",
      "topic_name_ar": "adverbs of frequency",
      "topic_name_en": "adverbs of frequency",
      "unit_id": "290f3fbe-d9ec-41cb-93d3-aa2401ee6c7c",
      "unit_number": 10
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم going to للتحدث عن الخطط والنوايا المستقبلية. نستخدم am/is/are حسب الفاعل، ثم going to، ثم الفعل في المصدر",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eGoing to\u003c/b\u003e is used to talk about future plans and intentions.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• I am going to post a photo on Instagram tomorrow.\u003cbr\u003e• She is going to watch YouTube videos tonight.\u003cbr\u003e• We are going to create a TikTok account next week.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen do we use 'going to'?\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. For plans we have already decided\u003cbr\u003e2. For things we intend to do in the future\u003cbr\u003e3. For predictions based on present evidence\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eStructure:\u003c/b\u003e We use the verb 'be' (am/is/are) + going to + base verb",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + am/is/are + going to + base verb",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "am going to upload",
                "sentence": "I am going to upload a video to YouTube.",
                "translation_ar": "سأقوم برفع فيديو على يوتيوب"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "are going to follow",
                "sentence": "They are going to follow me on Instagram.",
                "translation_ar": "سيقومون بمتابعتي على الإنستغرام"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "is going to share",
                "sentence": "He is going to share this post.",
                "translation_ar": "سيقوم بمشاركة هذا المنشور"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I am going to post a photo",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس فعل الكون am/is/are قبل going to",
                "wrong": "I going to post a photo"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She is going to post a story",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم الفعل في المصدر بعد going to وليس المضارع",
                "wrong": "She is going to posts a story"
              },
              {
                "correct": "We are going to make a video",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم going to وليس فقط go",
                "wrong": "We are go to make a video"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "ea8c8bfe-4ce7-46cb-afeb-2b37d0c51746",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Social Media",
      "topic_name_ar": "going to (future)",
      "topic_name_en": "going to (future)",
      "unit_id": "8bf43cee-3a7d-4d85-b33f-362c3dcc5f33",
      "unit_number": 11
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم want للتعبير عن الرغبة بشكل مباشر مع الأصدقاء والعائلة. نستخدم would like للتعبير عن الرغبة بأدب أكثر مع الغرباء أو في المحلات",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eWant vs Would like\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use \u003cb\u003ewant\u003c/b\u003e and \u003cb\u003ewould like\u003c/b\u003e to express desires and requests, but they have different levels of politeness.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• I want to recycle more plastic bottles.\u003cbr\u003e• I would like to start composting at home.\u003cbr\u003e• She wants to buy organic vegetables.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWant\u003c/b\u003e is more direct and informal. We use it with friends and family.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWould like\u003c/b\u003e is more polite and formal. We use it in shops, restaurants, or with strangers.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBoth can be followed by:\u003cbr\u003e• A noun: I want/would like some eco-friendly products\u003cbr\u003e• To + infinitive: I want/would like to plant a garden",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + want/would like + noun/to + infinitive",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "want to use",
                "sentence": "I want to use solar energy.",
                "translation_ar": "أريد أن أستخدم الطاقة الشمسية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "would like",
                "sentence": "We would like some organic food.",
                "translation_ar": "نود بعض الطعام العضوي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "want",
                "sentence": "They want a hybrid car.",
                "translation_ar": "يريدون سيارة هجينة"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I would like to plant trees",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس to قبل الفعل",
                "wrong": "I would like plant trees"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She wants to recycle",
                "explanation_ar": "أضف s مع الضمائر المفردة",
                "wrong": "She want to recycle"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I want to save water",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم to + infinitive وليس that + clause",
                "wrong": "I want that I save water"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "1a315e88-1b68-413a-8f28-515e5d4bee58",
      "level_id": "2755b494-c7ff-4bdc-96ac-7ab735dc038c",
      "level_number": 1,
      "theme_en": "Green Living",
      "topic_name_ar": "want/would like",
      "topic_name_en": "want/would like",
      "unit_id": "73c7463e-df09-452a-b369-41334805d8a6",
      "unit_number": 12
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "سنستخدم will للقرارات السريعة والوعود والتنبؤات المبنية على الرأي. سنستخدم going to للخطط المُعدة مسبقاً والتنبؤات المبنية على دليل واضح.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eWill vs Going to\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBoth 'will' and 'going to' talk about future actions, but we use them differently:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWILL:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Quick decisions (decide at the moment of speaking)\u003cbr\u003e• Predictions based on what we think\u003cbr\u003e• Promises and offers\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eGOING TO:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Plans we already made\u003cbr\u003e• Predictions based on evidence we can see\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eI will help you study for the memory test\u003c/i\u003e (quick decision/offer)\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eI'm going to practice brain exercises tomorrow\u003c/i\u003e (planned before)\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eShe will probably forget the answer\u003c/i\u003e (prediction/opinion)\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eLook at those notes! You're going to remember everything!\u003c/i\u003e (prediction with evidence)",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "WILL: Subject + will + base verb\u003cbr\u003eGOING TO: Subject + am/is/are + going to + base verb",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "will remember",
                "sentence": "I will remember your birthday next year.",
                "translation_ar": "سأتذكر عيد ميلادك العام القادم"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "is going to study",
                "sentence": "She is going to study memory techniques tonight.",
                "translation_ar": "ستدرس تقنيات الذاكرة الليلة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "will process",
                "sentence": "The brain will process this information quickly.",
                "translation_ar": "سيعالج الدماغ هذه المعلومات بسرعة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "are going to take",
                "sentence": "We are going to take a memory test tomorrow.",
                "translation_ar": "سنخوض اختبار ذاكرة غداً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I will study / I'm going to study",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نضع am/is/are قبل will",
                "wrong": "I'm will study"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I'm going to remember",
                "explanation_ar": "نحتاج am/is/are قبل going to دائماً",
                "wrong": "I going to remember"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She will forget",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نضع to بعد will",
                "wrong": "She will to forget"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "a0788c15-ac00-42b3-8f63-e1449b01e2c0",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Brain \u0026 Memory",
      "topic_name_ar": "will vs going to",
      "topic_name_en": "will vs going to",
      "unit_id": "542c8884-0fd4-4a0c-abad-d5f0913ab8b4",
      "unit_number": 1
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم المضارع التام مع ever/never للحديث عن التجارب في الحياة • ever = في أي وقت (للأسئلة والجمل المنفية) • never = لم يحدث أبداً (جملة إيجابية لكن معنى سلبي) • never لها معنى سلبي بالفعل فلا نضع معها not",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePresent Perfect with Ever/Never\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLook at these examples:\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eHave you ever seen a panda?\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eI have never visited a zoo with endangered species.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eShe has never heard of the Siberian tiger.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use the \u003cb\u003epresent perfect\u003c/b\u003e with \u003cb\u003eever\u003c/b\u003e and \u003cb\u003enever\u003c/b\u003e to talk about experiences in our life (from birth until now). We don't say exactly when these experiences happened.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eEver\u003c/b\u003e = at any time in your life (used in questions and negative sentences)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eNever\u003c/b\u003e = not at any time in your life (used in positive sentences but with negative meaning)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eImportant:\u003c/b\u003e 'Never' already has a negative meaning, so we don't use 'not' with it.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Have/Has + subject + ever + past participle? / Subject + have/has + never + past participle",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "Have you ever seen",
                "sentence": "Have you ever seen a snow leopard?",
                "translation_ar": "هل رأيت نمر الثلج من قبل؟"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "have never watched",
                "sentence": "I have never watched a documentary about whales.",
                "translation_ar": "لم أشاهد وثائقي عن الحيتان أبداً"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Has she ever heard",
                "sentence": "Has she ever heard about the black rhino?",
                "translation_ar": "هل سمعت عن وحيد القرن الأسود من قبل؟"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "have never visited",
                "sentence": "We have never visited a wildlife sanctuary.",
                "translation_ar": "لم نزر محمية طبيعية أبداً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I have never seen tigers",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم don't مع never - never كافية للنفي",
                "wrong": "I don't never see tigers"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Have you ever seen a panda?",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم المضارع التام وليس الماضي البسيط مع ever",
                "wrong": "Did you ever see a panda?"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I have never seen elephants",
                "explanation_ar": "نحتاج التصريف الثالث للفعل (past participle) مع المضارع التام",
                "wrong": "I have never see elephants"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Haven't you ever been to a zoo?",
                "explanation_ar": "للسؤال المنفي نستخدم Haven't + ever وليس Have + never",
                "wrong": "Have you never been to a zoo?"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "2f636b72-94c2-451a-924c-9a2fbc3a9b40",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Endangered Species",
      "topic_name_ar": "present perfect (ever/never)",
      "topic_name_en": "present perfect (ever/never)",
      "unit_id": "54c9c8f5-2e61-40be-be31-825a0cfc40f6",
      "unit_number": 2
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم المضارع التام مع just (للتو), already (بالفعل), yet (بعد) للربط بين الماضي والحاضر. Just و already تأتي بين have/has والفعل الثالث. Yet تأتي في نهاية الجملة مع النفي والاستفهام.",
            "content_en": "The Present Perfect with \u003cb\u003ejust\u003c/b\u003e, \u003cb\u003ealready\u003c/b\u003e, and \u003cb\u003eyet\u003c/b\u003e connects past actions to the present moment.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eJust\u003c/b\u003e = very recently (happened a short time ago)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eAlready\u003c/b\u003e = before now, sooner than expected\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eYet\u003c/b\u003e = until now (used in questions and negatives)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003ci\u003eJust\u003c/i\u003e and \u003ci\u003ealready\u003c/i\u003e go between 'have/has' and the past participle.\u003cbr\u003e\u003ci\u003eYet\u003c/i\u003e goes at the end of the sentence.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + have/has + just/already + past participle / Subject + have/has + not + past participle + yet",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "has just started",
                "sentence": "The storm has just started.",
                "translation_ar": "العاصفة بدأت للتو"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "have already prepared",
                "sentence": "We have already prepared for the hurricane.",
                "translation_ar": "لقد استعددنا بالفعل للإعصار"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "hasn't stopped yet",
                "sentence": "The rain hasn't stopped yet.",
                "translation_ar": "المطر لم يتوقف بعد"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I have just finished",
                "explanation_ar": "just تأتي بعد have/has وليس قبلها",
                "wrong": "I just have finished"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Have you finished your homework yet?",
                "explanation_ar": "yet تأتي في نهاية الجملة",
                "wrong": "Have you finished yet your homework?"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I have already gone",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم الفعل الثالث (past participle) وليس الماضي البسيط",
                "wrong": "I have already went"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "1cca8153-bcc9-4ad9-858c-302f0805704d",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Extreme Weather",
      "topic_name_ar": "present perfect (just/already/yet)",
      "topic_name_en": "present perfect (just/already/yet)",
      "unit_id": "6527e32e-b7f3-4196-9bae-a034712c9fa6",
      "unit_number": 3
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "المقارنات تستخدم لمقارنة شيئين أو شخصين • الصفات القصيرة: نضيف -er • الصفات الطويلة: نستخدم more + الصفة • لا تنسى استخدام than للمقارنة",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eComparatives\u003c/b\u003e are used to compare two things or people.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExample sentences:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• This dress is \u003cb\u003emore expensive\u003c/b\u003e than that one.\u003cbr\u003e• Sara is \u003cb\u003etaller\u003c/b\u003e than her sister.\u003cbr\u003e• These shoes are \u003cb\u003emore comfortable\u003c/b\u003e than my old ones.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eHow to form comparatives:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e1. Short adjectives (1 syllable):\u003c/b\u003e Add \u003cb\u003e-er\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• tall → taller\u003cbr\u003e• cheap → cheaper\u003cbr\u003e• smart → smarter\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e2. Short adjectives ending in -y:\u003c/b\u003e Change \u003cb\u003e-y to -ier\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• pretty → prettier\u003cbr\u003e• trendy → trendier\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e3. Long adjectives (2+ syllables):\u003c/b\u003e Use \u003cb\u003emore + adjective\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• beautiful → more beautiful\u003cbr\u003e• fashionable → more fashionable\u003cbr\u003e• expensive → more expensive\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eIrregular comparatives:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• good → better\u003cbr\u003e• bad → worse\u003cbr\u003e• far → farther/further\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eRemember to use \u003cb\u003e'than'\u003c/b\u003e when comparing: A is taller \u003cb\u003ethan\u003c/b\u003e B.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Short adjectives: adjective + -er + than\u003cbr\u003eLong adjectives: more + adjective + than",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "warmer than",
                "sentence": "This jacket is warmer than my old one.",
                "translation_ar": "هذه السترة أدفأ من القديمة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "more expensive than",
                "sentence": "Designer clothes are more expensive than regular clothes.",
                "translation_ar": "الملابس المصممة أغلى من الملابس العادية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "better than",
                "sentence": "My style is better than yours.",
                "translation_ar": "أسلوبي أفضل من أسلوبك"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "taller than",
                "explanation_ar": "الصفات القصيرة نضيف لها -er وليس more",
                "wrong": "more tall than"
              },
              {
                "correct": "more beautiful than",
                "explanation_ar": "الصفات الطويلة نستخدم معها more",
                "wrong": "beautifuler than"
              },
              {
                "correct": "better than",
                "explanation_ar": "better صيغة مقارنة شاذة لا نضيف معها more",
                "wrong": "better more than"
              },
              {
                "correct": "This dress is more expensive than that one",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم than وليس from في المقارنة",
                "wrong": "This dress is expensive from that one"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "a318bf47-9386-47d7-bf01-4b16088271d3",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
