      "unit_id": "8a656780-a4f2-4cf1-b44d-f74b9f65a05f",
      "unit_number": 4
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "صيغة التفضيل تُستخدم للمقارنة بين ثلاثة أشياء أو أكثر • الصفات القصيرة: نضيف the + est • الصفات الطويلة: نستخدم the most • صفات شاذة: good/best, bad/worst",
            "content_en": "Superlatives are used to compare three or more things and show which one has the most or least of a quality.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• The Great Wall of China is \u003cb\u003ethe longest\u003c/b\u003e wall in the world.\u003cbr\u003e• Cleopatra was \u003cb\u003ethe most famous\u003c/b\u003e queen of ancient Egypt.\u003cbr\u003e• This is \u003cb\u003ethe oldest\u003c/b\u003e hidden treasure ever found.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eHow to form superlatives:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eShort adjectives (1-2 syllables):\u003c/b\u003e Add 'the' + adjective + 'est'\u003cbr\u003eold → the oldest, long → the longest, big → the biggest\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eLong adjectives (3+ syllables):\u003c/b\u003e Use 'the most' + adjective\u003cbr\u003efamous → the most famous, interesting → the most interesting\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eIrregular adjectives:\u003c/b\u003e These change completely\u003cbr\u003egood → the best, bad → the worst, far → the farthest",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "the + adjective + est OR the most + adjective",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "the most mysterious",
                "sentence": "The pyramids are the most mysterious monuments in Egypt.",
                "translation_ar": "الأهرامات هي أكثر الآثار غموضاً في مصر"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "the richest",
                "sentence": "King Tutankhamun had the richest tomb in the Valley of Kings.",
                "translation_ar": "كان للملك توت عنخ آمون أغنى مقبرة في وادي الملوك"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "the smallest",
                "sentence": "This ancient coin is the smallest artifact in our collection.",
                "translation_ar": "هذه العملة القديمة هي أصغر قطعة أثرية في مجموعتنا"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "the oldest",
                "explanation_ar": "الصفات القصيرة تأخذ est وليس most",
                "wrong": "the most old"
              },
              {
                "correct": "the most famous",
                "explanation_ar": "الصفات الطويلة تحتاج most وليس est",
                "wrong": "the famousest"
              },
              {
                "correct": "the best",
                "explanation_ar": "good صفة شاذة تصبح best",
                "wrong": "the goodest"
              },
              {
                "correct": "the most beautiful",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس أداة التعريف the",
                "wrong": "most beautiful"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "e084cd8b-576f-45d6-9c66-3819347beb7a",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Hidden History",
      "topic_name_ar": "superlatives",
      "topic_name_en": "superlatives",
      "unit_id": "59de8aaa-16be-4f95-86f6-105c2310ab18",
      "unit_number": 5
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم should للنصيحة أو للتعبير عن الصواب والخطأ. should أقل قوة من must. لا نضيف s مع الضمائر، والفعل يبقى في المصدر",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eShould/Shouldn't\u003c/b\u003e is used to give advice or express what is right or wrong to do.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Cities should use clean energy to protect the environment.\u003cbr\u003e• People shouldn't throw garbage on smart city streets.\u003cbr\u003e• Future cities should have more green spaces.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen to use Should/Shouldn't:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e- To give advice or recommendations\u003cbr\u003e- To say what is right or wrong\u003cbr\u003e- To express obligation (but softer than 'must')\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eForm:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Positive: Subject + should + base verb\u003cbr\u003e• Negative: Subject + shouldn't + base verb\u003cbr\u003e• Question: Should + subject + base verb?",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + should/shouldn't + base verb",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "should have",
                "sentence": "Smart cities should have efficient public transport.",
                "translation_ar": "يجب أن تمتلك المدن الذكية وسائل نقل عام فعالة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "shouldn't waste",
                "sentence": "We shouldn't waste water in future cities.",
                "translation_ar": "يجب ألا نهدر المياه في مدن المستقبل"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Should cities use",
                "sentence": "Should cities use solar panels for energy?",
                "translation_ar": "هل يجب أن تستخدم المدن الألواح الشمسية للطاقة؟"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Cities should have clean air.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم to بعد should",
                "wrong": "Cities should to have clean air."
              },
              {
                "correct": "He should go to the smart city.",
                "explanation_ar": "الفعل بعد should يبقى في المصدر بدون إضافات",
                "wrong": "He should goes to the smart city."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Shouldn't cities be green?",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم shouldn't كاختصار في الأسئلة",
                "wrong": "Should not cities be green?"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "deb24c94-db05-4c1a-aa74-8ef6daa3bd75",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Future Cities",
      "topic_name_ar": "should/shouldnt",
      "topic_name_en": "should/shouldnt",
      "unit_id": "5366f092-2222-42fa-8128-c7e4d81a762e",
      "unit_number": 6
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "must و have to كلاهما يعبر عن الالتزام أو الضرورة. must للقواعد والآراء الشخصية القوية، have to للالتزامات الخارجية والظروف. must not تعني الممنوع، don't have to تعني غير ضروري (اختياري)",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eMust\u003c/b\u003e and \u003cb\u003ehave to\u003c/b\u003e both express obligation or necessity, but they are used differently:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eMUST\u003c/b\u003e is used for:\u003cbr\u003e• Rules and regulations\u003cbr\u003e• Strong personal opinions about what is necessary\u003cbr\u003e• Internal obligations (what we think is important)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eHAVE TO\u003c/b\u003e is used for:\u003cbr\u003e• External obligations (rules from others)\u003cbr\u003e• Facts and circumstances that force us to do something\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBoth \u003ci\u003emust\u003c/i\u003e and \u003ci\u003ehave to\u003c/i\u003e have the same meaning in positive sentences, but \u003cb\u003emust not\u003c/b\u003e means prohibition (forbidden), while \u003cb\u003edon't have to\u003c/b\u003e means not necessary (you can choose).",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + must + base verb\u003cbr\u003eSubject + have/has to + base verb\u003cbr\u003eSubject + must not + base verb (prohibition)\u003cbr\u003eSubject + don't/doesn't have to + base verb (not necessary)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "must turn off",
                "sentence": "I must turn off my phone during the digital detox weekend.",
                "translation_ar": "يجب أن أغلق هاتفي خلال عطلة نهاية الأسبوع للتخلص من الرقمية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "have to check",
                "sentence": "We have to check our emails because our boss requires it.",
                "translation_ar": "علينا أن نتحقق من إيميلاتنا لأن المدير يطلب ذلك"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "must not use",
                "sentence": "You must not use social media during the digital detox challenge.",
                "translation_ar": "يُمنع عليك استخدام وسائل التواصل الاجتماعي خلال تحدي التخلص الرقمي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "don't have to delete",
                "sentence": "You don't have to delete your apps, just avoid using them.",
                "translation_ar": "لست مضطراً لحذف تطبيقاتك، فقط تجنب استخدامها"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I must check my phone",
                "explanation_ar": "must لا يتبعها to، بل الفعل مباشرة",
                "wrong": "I must to check my phone"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She must turn off WiFi",
                "explanation_ar": "must لا تتغير مع الضمائر المختلفة",
                "wrong": "She musts turn off WiFi"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I must not use Instagram",
                "explanation_ar": "النفي مع must يكون must not وليس don't must",
                "wrong": "I don't must use Instagram"
              },
              {
                "correct": "We have to turn off notifications",
                "explanation_ar": "have to وليس have فقط",
                "wrong": "We have turn off notifications"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "a13f30db-6d74-4203-9094-ef542bf37ae7",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Digital Detox",
      "topic_name_ar": "must/have to",
      "topic_name_en": "must/have to",
      "unit_id": "d079ba8b-e738-49fe-8c2b-f3b82a4cdf68",
      "unit_number": 7
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "may و might يستخدمان للتعبير عن الاحتمالية. may تعبر عن احتمالية أقوى، might تعبر عن احتمالية أضعف. كلاهما يأتي بعده الفعل في المصدر بدون to",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eMay and Might\u003c/b\u003e are modal verbs used to express possibility or probability.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• It \u003cb\u003emay\u003c/b\u003e rain on our mountain hike tomorrow.\u003cbr\u003e• The trail \u003cb\u003emight\u003c/b\u003e be closed due to snow.\u003cbr\u003e• We \u003cb\u003emay\u003c/b\u003e reach the summit before sunset.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eUse:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eMay\u003c/b\u003e = stronger possibility (about 50-70% chance)\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eMight\u003c/b\u003e = weaker possibility (about 30-50% chance)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBoth can be used for present or future possibilities. In spoken English, the difference is often small.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + may/might + base verb (without 'to')",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "may change",
                "sentence": "The weather may change in the mountains.",
                "translation_ar": "قد يتغير الطقس في الجبال"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "might see",
                "sentence": "We might see eagles during our climb.",
                "translation_ar": "قد نرى نسوراً أثناء تسلقنا"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "may cancel",
                "sentence": "The guide may cancel the trip if it's too windy.",
                "translation_ar": "قد يلغي المرشد الرحلة إذا كانت الرياح قوية جداً"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "might need",
                "sentence": "You might need warmer clothes at the peak.",
                "translation_ar": "قد تحتاج ملابس أدفأ في القمة"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "It may rain",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نضع 'to' بعد may/might",
                "wrong": "It may to rain"
              },
              {
                "correct": "We might be late",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم المصدر بدون 'to' بعد might، ليس الفعل المصرف",
                "wrong": "We might are late"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The mountain may be dangerous",
                "explanation_ar": "may/might لا تتغير مع الضمائر المختلفة",
                "wrong": "The mountain mays be dangerous"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "84e15ea7-afcf-4a01-8e44-e0c7e29f3c23",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Mountain Adventures",
      "topic_name_ar": "may/might",
      "topic_name_en": "may/might",
      "unit_id": "301187bb-9088-4bfa-b3e2-5dabd93bb0b4",
      "unit_number": 8
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم too للتعبير عن الزيادة المفرطة (مشكلة)، و enough للتعبير عن الكمية الكافية. too تأتي قبل الصفة، enough تأتي بعد الصفة وقبل الاسم",
            "content_en": "We use \u003cb\u003etoo\u003c/b\u003e and \u003cb\u003eenough\u003c/b\u003e to talk about quantity and degree.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eTOO\u003c/b\u003e means 'more than necessary' or 'more than good' - it shows a problem or negative result.\u003cbr\u003e• The movie was \u003cb\u003etoo long\u003c/b\u003e. I fell asleep.\u003cbr\u003e• The cinema tickets are \u003cb\u003etoo expensive\u003c/b\u003e for students.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eENOUGH\u003c/b\u003e means 'sufficient' or 'as much as necessary' - it can be positive or negative.\u003cbr\u003e• This film is funny \u003cb\u003eenough\u003c/b\u003e for children.\u003cbr\u003e• We don't have \u003cb\u003eenough money\u003c/b\u003e to buy popcorn.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eTOO\u003c/b\u003e comes before adjectives and adverbs.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eENOUGH\u003c/b\u003e comes after adjectives/adverbs, but before nouns.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "TOO + adjective/adverb\u003cbr\u003eAdjective/adverb + ENOUGH\u003cbr\u003eENOUGH + noun",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "too scary",
                "sentence": "The horror movie was too scary for me.",
                "translation_ar": "فيلم الرعب كان مخيفاً جداً بالنسبة لي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "loud enough",
                "sentence": "The sound in the cinema isn't loud enough.",
                "translation_ar": "الصوت في السينما ليس عالياً بما فيه الكفاية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "enough time",
                "sentence": "We have enough time to watch another film.",
                "translation_ar": "لدينا وقت كافٍ لمشاهدة فيلم آخر"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "too quickly",
                "sentence": "The actor spoke too quickly in that scene.",
                "translation_ar": "تحدث الممثل بسرعة مفرطة في ذلك المشهد"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "The movie was long enough.",
                "explanation_ar": "enough تأتي بعد الصفة وليس قبلها",
                "wrong": "The movie was enough long."
              },
              {
                "correct": "We have enough time.",
                "explanation_ar": "مع الأسماء، enough تأتي قبل الاسم",
                "wrong": "We have time enough."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The film is too boring.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم very مع too معاً",
                "wrong": "The film is very too boring."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "b52bca72-f366-4661-a1ce-46ce99535be7",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Film \u0026 Cinema",
      "topic_name_ar": "too/enough",
      "topic_name_en": "too/enough",
      "unit_id": "8b9c8041-693a-42bb-8bbd-f2b79a3851bd",
      "unit_number": 9
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الجيرند (verb + ing) يُستخدم بعد أفعال معينة وكفاعل للجملة. المصدر (to + verb) يُستخدم بعد أفعال أخرى وللتعبير عن الهدف. يجب حفظ الأفعال التي تأتي مع كل نوع.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eGerunds vs Infinitives - Basic Rules\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLook at these examples:\u003cbr\u003e• I enjoy \u003cb\u003esaving\u003c/b\u003e water. (gerund)\u003cbr\u003e• We need \u003cb\u003eto protect\u003c/b\u003e our rivers. (infinitive)\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eDrinking\u003c/b\u003e clean water is important. (gerund as subject)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhat are they?\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eGerund\u003c/b\u003e = verb + ing (saving, drinking, swimming)\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eInfinitive\u003c/b\u003e = to + base verb (to save, to drink, to swim)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen to use Gerunds (-ing):\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. After certain verbs: enjoy, like, love, hate, stop, finish\u003cbr\u003e2. As the subject of a sentence\u003cbr\u003e3. After prepositions\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen to use Infinitives (to + verb):\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. After certain verbs: want, need, plan, decide, hope, try\u003cbr\u003e2. To express purpose (why we do something)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eRemember:\u003c/b\u003e Some verbs are always followed by gerunds, others by infinitives. You need to memorize which verbs take which form!",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Gerund: Subject + verb + (verb + ing) | Infinitive: Subject + verb + (to + base verb)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "enjoy swimming",
                "sentence": "Children enjoy swimming in clean rivers.",
                "translation_ar": "يستمتع الأطفال بالسباحة في الأنهار النظيفة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "want to save",
                "sentence": "We want to save water every day.",
                "translation_ar": "نريد أن نوفر الماء كل يوم"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Protecting",
                "sentence": "Protecting water sources is everyone's responsibility.",
                "translation_ar": "حماية مصادر المياه مسؤولية الجميع"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I want to save water.",
                "explanation_ar": "الفعل want يأتي دائماً مع المصدر (to + verb) وليس الجيرند",
                "wrong": "I want saving water."
              },
              {
                "correct": "I enjoy swimming.",
                "explanation_ar": "الفعل enjoy يأتي دائماً مع الجيرند (verb + ing) وليس المصدر",
                "wrong": "I enjoy to swim."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Drinking water is important.",
                "explanation_ar": "كفاعل للجملة، نستخدم الجيرند عادة وليس المصدر",
                "wrong": "To drink water is important."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "5f7249a7-5fac-4ec0-92ea-4556d2b5446a",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Water Crisis",
      "topic_name_ar": "gerund vs infinitive basics",
      "topic_name_en": "gerund vs infinitive basics",
      "unit_id": "6d85610d-0017-4f28-978e-f1281edc75e6",
      "unit_number": 10
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الشرط الأول يُستخدم للحديث عن المواقف المستقبلية الممكنة ونتائجها. نستخدمه عندما نعتقد أن شيئاً ما قد يحدث في المستقبل.",
            "content_en": "The first conditional is used to talk about \u003cb\u003epossible future situations\u003c/b\u003e and their results. We use it when we think something might happen in the future.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe first conditional has two parts:\u003cbr\u003e- \u003cb\u003eIf clause\u003c/b\u003e (condition): uses present simple\u003cbr\u003e- \u003cb\u003eMain clause\u003c/b\u003e (result): uses will + base verb\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe can start with either the if clause or the main clause. When we start with the if clause, we use a comma before the main clause.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "If + present simple, will + base verb OR will + base verb + if + present simple",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "If you paint",
                "sentence": "If you paint graffiti on that wall, you will get in trouble.",
                "translation_ar": "إذا رسمت الجرافيتي على ذلك الجدار، ستواجه مشاكل"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "will look amazing if we use",
                "sentence": "The street art will look amazing if we use bright colors.",
                "translation_ar": "سيبدو فن الشارع رائعاً إذا استخدمنا ألواناً زاهية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "If the artist finishes",
                "sentence": "If the artist finishes the mural today, we will celebrate tonight.",
                "translation_ar": "إذا انتهى الفنان من الجدارية اليوم، سنحتفل الليلة"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "If you paint the wall, I will help you.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم will في جملة الشرط (if clause)",
                "wrong": "If you will paint the wall, I will help you."
              },
              {
                "correct": "If he paints graffiti, he will get arrested.",
                "explanation_ar": "نحتاج فاصلة عندما نبدأ بجملة الشرط",
                "wrong": "If he paints graffiti he will get arrested."
              },
              {
                "correct": "If she finishes the artwork, we will display it.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم المضارع البسيط في جملة الشرط (تحتاج s مع الضمير she)",
                "wrong": "If she finish the artwork, we will display it."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "47c58d9b-a322-4bbd-97a7-7bb4bea83426",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Street Art",
      "topic_name_ar": "first conditional",
      "topic_name_en": "first conditional",
      "unit_id": "daf340b3-7268-44b3-ad0d-4a62ab8d0d21",
      "unit_number": 11
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الماضي المستمر يصف الأحداث التي كانت تحدث في وقت معين في الماضي. يستخدم لوصف الأحداث المتقطعة أو الخلفية في القصص",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePast Continuous Tense\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe past continuous describes actions that were \u003cb\u003ehappening\u003c/b\u003e or \u003cb\u003ein progress\u003c/b\u003e at a specific time in the past. We often use it to set the scene for past events or describe interrupted actions.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen to use:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Actions in progress at a specific past time\u003cbr\u003e• Background actions in stories\u003cbr\u003e• Interrupted actions (with simple past)\u003cbr\u003e• Simultaneous past actions\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eTime expressions:\u003c/b\u003e at 3pm yesterday, while, when, all day, during the trip",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + was/were + verb-ing",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "was traveling",
                "sentence": "Marco Polo was traveling through Asia when he discovered new spices.",
                "translation_ar": "كان ماركو بولو يسافر عبر آسيا عندما اكتشف توابل جديدة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "were crossing",
                "sentence": "The explorers were crossing the desert at midnight.",
                "translation_ar": "كان المستكشفون يعبرون الصحراء في منتصف الليل"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "was climbing",
                "sentence": "While she was climbing Mount Everest, it started snowing.",
                "translation_ar": "بينما كانت تتسلق جبل إيفرست، بدأ الثلج يتساقط"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I was going to the market",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم الفعل مع -ing وليس المصدر",
                "wrong": "I was go to the market"
              },
              {
                "correct": "They were traveling together",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم were مع الجمع وليس was",
                "wrong": "They was traveling together"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She was walking alone",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم was مع المفرد وليس were",
                "wrong": "She were walking alone"
              },
              {
                "correct": "We were visiting the museum",
                "explanation_ar": "We يتطلب were دائماً",
                "wrong": "We was visiting the museum"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "c827f7ac-1a9a-44f6-8cfc-1a00268189f0",
      "level_id": "d3349438-8c8e-46b6-9ee6-e2e01c23229d",
      "level_number": 2,
      "theme_en": "Remarkable Journeys",
      "topic_name_ar": "past continuous",
      "topic_name_en": "past continuous",
      "unit_id": "82167f9b-2eff-4a0b-aa9f-ca7f4cec885a",
      "unit_number": 12
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الماضي البسيط: للأحداث المنتهية في وقت محدد في الماضي • الماضي التام: للأحداث التي حدثت في الماضي لكن لها تأثير على الحاضر • استخدم الماضي التام مع: since, for, already, yet • استخدم الماضي البسيط مع: yesterday, ago, last week",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePresent Perfect vs Past Simple\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• AI technology \u003cb\u003ehas changed\u003c/b\u003e our lives dramatically. (focus on the result now)\u003cbr\u003e• Scientists \u003cb\u003edeveloped\u003c/b\u003e the first AI program in 1956. (specific time in the past)\u003cbr\u003e• ChatGPT \u003cb\u003ehas become\u003c/b\u003e very popular since its launch. (from past until now)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen to use Present Perfect:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e- Actions that happened at an unspecified time in the past but are relevant now\u003cbr\u003e- Actions that started in the past and continue to the present\u003cbr\u003e- Recent actions with present results\u003cbr\u003e- With words like: since, for, already, yet, just, ever, never\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen to use Past Simple:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e- Actions completed at a specific time in the past\u003cbr\u003e- Sequential actions in the past\u003cbr\u003e- With time expressions like: yesterday, last week, in 2020, ago, when",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Present Perfect: Subject + have/has + past participle | Past Simple: Subject + verb (past form)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "has revolutionized",
                "sentence": "Machine learning has revolutionized data analysis.",
                "translation_ar": "لقد أحدث التعلم الآلي ثورة في تحليل البيانات"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "launched",
                "sentence": "Google launched its AI assistant in 2016.",
                "translation_ar": "أطلقت جوجل مساعدها الذكي في عام 2016"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "have been tested",
                "sentence": "Self-driving cars have been tested for several years.",
                "translation_ar": "تم اختبار السيارات ذاتية القيادة لعدة سنوات"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "created",
                "sentence": "IBM created Deep Blue twenty years ago.",
                "translation_ar": "أنشأت آي بي إم ديب بلو قبل عشرين عاماً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I visited the AI conference last week.",
                "explanation_ar": "مع الوقت المحدد (last week) نستخدم الماضي البسيط",
                "wrong": "I have visited the AI conference last week."
              },
              {
                "correct": "AI technology has changed our lives.",
                "explanation_ar": "عندما نتحدث عن تأثير مستمر حتى الآن نستخدم الماضي التام",
                "wrong": "AI technology changed our lives."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Have you ever used AI tools?",
                "explanation_ar": "مع ever نستخدم الماضي التام وليس الماضي البسيط",
                "wrong": "Did you ever use AI tools?"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "32bbd048-f3d1-432f-b3b0-ea60eee1eba7",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Artificial Intelligence",
      "topic_name_ar": "present perfect vs past simple",
      "topic_name_en": "present perfect vs past simple",
      "unit_id": "a5b583a4-5d9e-41b7-b95f-c07e0c44f64b",
      "unit_number": 1
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم هذا الزمن للتحدث عن الأفعال التي بدأت في الماضي ومازالت مستمرة، أو الأنشطة الحديثة التي لها نتائج حاضرة. التركيز على استمرارية الفعل وليس فقط النتيجة.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePresent Perfect Continuous\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLook at these examples:\u003cbr\u003e• Marine biologists \u003cb\u003ehave been studying\u003c/b\u003e coral reefs for decades.\u003cbr\u003e• The coral \u003cb\u003ehas been growing\u003c/b\u003e slowly in this area.\u003cbr\u003e• Scientists \u003cb\u003ehave been monitoring\u003c/b\u003e the reef's health recently.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use the Present Perfect Continuous to talk about:\u003cbr\u003e1. Actions that started in the past and continue now\u003cbr\u003e2. Recent activities with present results\u003cbr\u003e3. Actions that happened repeatedly from past to present\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis tense emphasizes the \u003ci\u003eduration\u003c/i\u003e or \u003ci\u003econtinuation\u003c/i\u003e of the action, not just the result.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + have/has + been + verb-ing",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "have been researching",
                "sentence": "Marine scientists have been researching coral bleaching for years.",
                "translation_ar": "علماء البحار يبحثون في ابيضاض المرجان منذ سنوات"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "has been rising",
                "sentence": "The water temperature has been rising gradually.",
                "translation_ar": "درجة حرارة الماء ترتفع تدريجياً"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "have been documenting",
                "sentence": "Divers have been documenting the reef's condition since 2020.",
                "translation_ar": "الغواصون يوثقون حالة الشعاب منذ عام 2020"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Scientists have been studying coral reefs.",
                "explanation_ar": "يجب إضافة ing للفعل الرئيسي",
                "wrong": "Scientists have been study coral reefs."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The reef has been growing for centuries.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم الفعل مع ing وليس التصريف الثالث",
                "wrong": "The reef has been grew for centuries."
              },
              {
                "correct": "They have been working on this project since last month.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس إضافة ing للفعل",
                "wrong": "They have been work on this project since last month."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "29b4de00-3384-46c9-877c-3430a185227a",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Coral Reefs",
      "topic_name_ar": "present perfect continuous",
      "topic_name_en": "present perfect continuous",
      "unit_id": "55d40057-1d91-4eb0-8d78-b3f47a8d0a24",
      "unit_number": 2
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الشرط الثاني يُستخدم للحديث عن المواقف الخيالية أو غير الحقيقية في الحاضر أو المستقبل. هذه مواقف من غير المرجح أن تحدث أو مستحيلة الحدوث",
            "content_en": "The Second Conditional is used to talk about \u003cb\u003eimaginary or unreal situations\u003c/b\u003e in the present or future. These are situations that are unlikely to happen or impossible.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use it to:\u003cbr\u003e• Talk about hypothetical situations\u003cbr\u003e• Give advice\u003cbr\u003e• Express wishes about present situations\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe Second Conditional has two parts:\u003cbr\u003e1. \u003cb\u003eIf clause\u003c/b\u003e (condition) - uses past simple\u003cbr\u003e2. \u003cb\u003eMain clause\u003c/b\u003e (result) - uses would + base verb\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNote: We use \u003ci\u003ewere\u003c/i\u003e for all persons with the verb 'be' in formal English.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "If + subject + past simple, subject + would + base verb",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "could predict, would save",
                "sentence": "If scientists could predict earthquakes perfectly, they would save thousands of lives.",
                "translation_ar": "لو استطاع العلماء التنبؤ بالزلازل بشكل مثالي، لأنقذوا آلاف الأرواح"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "were, would study",
                "sentence": "If I were a seismologist, I would study earthquake patterns all day.",
                "translation_ar": "لو كنت عالم زلازل، لدرست أنماط الزلازل طوال اليوم"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "would feel, were",
                "sentence": "People would feel safer if buildings were more earthquake-resistant.",
                "translation_ar": "سيشعر الناس بأمان أكبر لو كانت المباني أكثر مقاومة للزلازل"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "If I were a seismologist...",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم 'were' مع جميع الضمائر في الشرط الثاني",
                "wrong": "If I was a seismologist..."
              },
              {
                "correct": "If earthquakes were predictable...",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم 'will' في جملة الشرط، بل الماضي البسيط",
                "wrong": "If earthquakes will be predictable..."
              },
              {
                "correct": "If we could predict earthquakes, we would save lives.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم 'would' وليس 'will' في جملة النتيجة",
                "wrong": "If we could predict earthquakes, we will save lives."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "c9da1354-fb67-42af-b281-e087565fa060",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Earthquake Science",
      "topic_name_ar": "second conditional",
      "topic_name_en": "second conditional",
      "unit_id": "85aabed1-aa8e-4ea6-9b58-bff1bbe4f9a8",
      "unit_number": 3
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الصوت المبني للمجهول يركز على الفعل أو متلقي الفعل، وليس على فاعل الفعل. نستخدمه عندما يكون الفاعل غير معروف أو غير مهم، أو عندما نريد التركيز على النتيجة أو العملية.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003ePassive Voice (Present)\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLook at these examples:\u003cbr\u003e• Coffee \u003cb\u003eis grown\u003c/b\u003e in Ethiopia.\u003cbr\u003e• Espresso machines \u003cb\u003eare used\u003c/b\u003e in Italian cafés.\u003cbr\u003e• Turkish coffee \u003cb\u003eis prepared\u003c/b\u003e with special techniques.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIn passive voice, we focus on the \u003ci\u003eaction\u003c/i\u003e or the \u003ci\u003ereceiver\u003c/i\u003e of the action, not who does it. We use passive voice when:\u003cbr\u003e• The doer is unknown or not important\u003cbr\u003e• We want to focus on the result/process\u003cbr\u003e• In formal writing or scientific descriptions\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eFormation:\u003c/b\u003e Subject + am/is/are + past participle\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe past participle is usually the same as the past simple for regular verbs (work→worked), but irregular verbs have special forms (make→made, grow→grown).",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + am/is/are + past participle",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "is grown",
                "sentence": "Coffee is grown in many countries.",
                "translation_ar": "تُزرع القهوة في دول كثيرة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "are made",
                "sentence": "Cappuccinos are made with steamed milk.",
                "translation_ar": "تُصنع الكابتشينو بالحليب المبخر"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "are roasted",
                "sentence": "The beans are roasted at high temperatures.",
                "translation_ar": "تُحمص الحبوب في درجات حرارة عالية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "is sold",
                "sentence": "Fair trade coffee is sold in supermarkets.",
                "translation_ar": "تُباع قهوة التجارة العادلة في السوبر ماركت"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Coffee is grown in Brazil.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم past participle وليس المصدر",
                "wrong": "Coffee is grow in Brazil."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Lattes are made with milk.",
                "explanation_ar": "الفعل غير النظامي make يصبح made",
                "wrong": "Lattes are make with milk."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Coffee beans are processed carefully.",
                "explanation_ar": "beans جمع، لذا نستخدم are",
                "wrong": "Coffee beans is processed carefully."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Turkish coffee is prepared with sugar.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس فعل المساعدة am/is/are",
                "wrong": "Turkish coffee prepared with sugar."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "0179cf9e-17d9-4527-8f70-be91f2956974",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Global Coffee Culture",
      "topic_name_ar": "passive voice (present)",
      "topic_name_en": "passive voice (present)",
      "unit_id": "738ff234-070d-4ace-9901-434e43521bdb",
      "unit_number": 4
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الصوت المبني للمجهول في الماضي يستخدم للتركيز على الفعل أو الشيء المتأثر بالفعل وليس الفاعل. نستخدم was/were + التصريف الثالث للفعل",
            "content_en": "The \u003cb\u003epassive voice (past)\u003c/b\u003e is used when we want to focus on the action or the person/thing that received the action, rather than who did it.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIn passive voice, the object of an active sentence becomes the subject. We use \u003cb\u003ewas/were + past participle\u003c/b\u003e to form the past passive.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWhen to use:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• When the doer is unknown or not important\u003cbr\u003e• When we want to emphasize what happened to something\u003cbr\u003e• In formal writing and reports\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eStructure:\u003c/b\u003e Subject + was/were + past participle (+ by + agent)",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + was/were + past participle (+ by + agent)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "were installed",
                "sentence": "The solar panels were installed last month.",
                "translation_ar": "تم تركيب الألواح الشمسية الشهر الماضي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "was discovered",
                "sentence": "Wind energy was discovered centuries ago.",
                "translation_ar": "تم اكتشاف طاقة الرياح منذ قرون"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "was built by the government",
                "sentence": "The hydroelectric dam was built by the government in 2015.",
                "translation_ar": "تم بناء السد الكهرومائي من قبل الحكومة في 2015"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "The solar panels were installed yesterday.",
                "explanation_ar": "نحتاج was/were مع التصريف الثالث في الماضي المبني للمجهول",
                "wrong": "The solar panels installed yesterday."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Wind turbines were constructed last year.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم were مع الجمع وليس was",
                "wrong": "Wind turbines was constructed last year."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The project was built in 2020.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم التصريف الثالث built وليس building في المبني للمجهول",
                "wrong": "The project was building in 2020."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "7b880f9b-ecdd-4fc8-89f1-aacab8cf8576",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Renewable Energy",
      "topic_name_ar": "passive voice (past)",
      "topic_name_en": "passive voice (past)",
      "unit_id": "79f8500f-f110-4b61-9099-15348ce19d79",
      "unit_number": 5
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الجمل الوصلية تعطي معلومات إضافية عن شخص أو شيء. نستخدم who للأشخاص، which للأشياء، و that للاثنين معاً",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eRelative clauses\u003c/b\u003e give us more information about a person or thing. We use relative pronouns to connect the extra information to the main sentence.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003ewho\u003c/b\u003e for people\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003ewhich\u003c/b\u003e for things/objects\u003cbr\u003e• Use \u003cb\u003ethat\u003c/b\u003e for both people and things (more informal)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe relative clause comes directly after the noun it describes. It helps us identify which person or thing we're talking about without starting a new sentence.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Main clause + relative pronoun (who/which/that) + additional information",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "who created this VR game",
                "sentence": "The developer who created this VR game is very talented.",
                "translation_ar": "المطور الذي أنشأ هذه اللعبة الافتراضية موهوب جداً"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "which I bought yesterday",
                "sentence": "The VR headset which I bought yesterday is amazing.",
                "translation_ar": "نظارة الواقع الافتراضي التي اشتريتها أمس رائعة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "that millions of users explore daily",
                "sentence": "This is the virtual world that millions of users explore daily.",
                "translation_ar": "هذا هو العالم الافتراضي الذي يستكشفه ملايين المستخدمين يومياً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "The person who designed the VR system",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم who للأشخاص، ليس which",
                "wrong": "The person which designed the VR system"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The VR game which/that I played",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم which أو that للأشياء، ليس who",
                "wrong": "The VR game who I played"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The user who loves VR technology",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تكرر الضمير بعد الضمير الوصلي",
                "wrong": "The user that he loves VR technology"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "e3e6fb5e-6257-4ef4-9c42-cc2efc167d8c",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Virtual Reality",
      "topic_name_ar": "relative clauses (who/which/that)",
      "topic_name_en": "relative clauses (who/which/that)",
      "unit_id": "aa6e8325-b825-4c0a-8218-b8a5341fc604",
      "unit_number": 6
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الكلام المنقول هو نقل ما قاله شخص آخر بدون استخدام كلماته الحرفية. نحتاج لتغيير الضمائر والأزمنة وإزالة علامات التنصيص. نضيف 'that' ونغير الفعل خطوة واحدة للماضي عادة.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eReported Speech (Indirect Speech)\u003c/b\u003e is when we tell someone what another person said, without using their exact words.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Direct: The psychologist said, \"Fear is a natural emotion.\"\u003cbr\u003e• Reported: The psychologist said that fear is a natural emotion.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Direct: \"I am afraid of spiders,\" she told me.\u003cbr\u003e• Reported: She told me that she was afraid of spiders.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eKey Changes in Reported Speech:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. Remove quotation marks\u003cbr\u003e2. Add 'that' (optional but recommended)\u003cbr\u003e3. Change pronouns (I → he/she, you → I/they)\u003cbr\u003e4. Change verb tenses (usually one step back in time)\u003cbr\u003e5. Change time expressions if necessary\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eCommon Tense Changes:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Present Simple → Past Simple\u003cbr\u003e• Present Continuous → Past Continuous\u003cbr\u003e• Past Simple → Past Perfect\u003cbr\u003e• Will → Would\u003cbr\u003e• Can → Could",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + said/told + (that) + reported clause with changed tense/pronouns",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "said that phobias were",
                "sentence": "The therapist said that phobias were treatable conditions.",
                "translation_ar": "قال المعالج أن الرهاب حالات قابلة للعلاج"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "told me that she couldn't",
                "sentence": "She told me that she couldn't sleep after watching horror movies.",
                "translation_ar": "أخبرتني أنها لا تستطيع النوم بعد مشاهدة أفلام الرعب"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "reported that stress hormones would increase",
                "sentence": "The researcher reported that stress hormones would increase during scary situations.",
                "translation_ar": "أفاد الباحث أن هرمونات التوتر تزداد في المواقف المخيفة"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "He said that he was scared",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم علامات التنصيص في الكلام المنقول ونغير الضمير",
                "wrong": "He said that 'I am scared'"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She said that she had nightmares",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم 'said' مع 'that' أو 'told + object'",
                "wrong": "She told that she has nightmares"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The doctor said I would feel better",
                "explanation_ar": "نغير 'will' إلى 'would' في الكلام المنقول",
                "wrong": "The doctor said I will feel better"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "5acaf976-73ae-4db8-8b9b-d2fbba9ab523",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Psychology of Fear",
      "topic_name_ar": "reported speech basics",
      "topic_name_en": "reported speech basics",
      "unit_id": "97b187e9-39e6-4263-8ed8-72a63e69273c",
      "unit_number": 7
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم 'used to' للتحدث عن عادات أو حقائق في الماضي لم تعد موجودة الآن. إنها تُظهر الفرق بين الماضي والحاضر.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eUsed to\u003c/b\u003e is used to talk about past habits or situations that were true in the past but are not true now.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExamples:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Ancient Romans \u003cb\u003eused to build\u003c/b\u003e aqueducts to transport water across long distances.\u003cbr\u003e• The Great Wall of China \u003cb\u003eused to protect\u003c/b\u003e the country from invasions.\u003cbr\u003e• People \u003cb\u003edidn't use to have\u003c/b\u003e modern machinery for construction.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eImportant:\u003c/b\u003e We use 'used to' for things that happened regularly in the past or were true for a long period, but are finished now. It shows a contrast between past and present.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + used to + base verb (positive)\u003cbr\u003eSubject + didn't use to + base verb (negative)\u003cbr\u003eDid + subject + use to + base verb? (question)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "used to move",
                "sentence": "Ancient Egyptians used to move massive stone blocks using wooden rollers.",
                "translation_ar": "كان المصريون القدماء ينقلون الكتل الحجرية الضخمة باستخدام البكرات الخشبية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "didn't use to have",
                "sentence": "Roman engineers didn't use to have concrete as strong as modern concrete.",
                "translation_ar": "لم يكن لدى المهندسين الرومان خرسانة قوية مثل الخرسانة الحديثة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Did... use to work",
                "sentence": "Did ancient builders use to work without safety equipment?",
                "translation_ar": "هل كان البناؤون القدماء يعملون بدون معدات أمان؟"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "They used to build pyramids.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم 'were' مع 'used to' - فقط 'used to' مباشرة",
                "wrong": "They were used to build pyramids."
              },
              {
                "correct": "They didn't use to have machines.",
                "explanation_ar": "في النفي نستخدم 'use' وليس 'used' بعد didn't",
                "wrong": "They didn't used to have machines."
              },
              {
                "correct": "They used to build temples.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم الفعل في المصدر بعد 'used to' وليس الماضي",
                "wrong": "They used to built temples."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "3470ea46-d3ef-49bc-9a15-3a336e3813fc",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Ancient Engineering",
      "topic_name_ar": "used to",
      "topic_name_en": "used to",
      "unit_id": "a12ff640-eb7e-4c48-8cf7-69f0f2cef190",
      "unit_number": 8
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "be used to = متعود على شيء الآن (حالة حاضرة)\nget used to = عملية التعود على شيء (تغيير وتكيف)\nكلاهما يتبع بـ اسم أو فعل + ing وليس المصدر",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eGet used to\u003c/b\u003e and \u003cb\u003ebe used to\u003c/b\u003e both talk about becoming familiar or comfortable with something.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eBe used to\u003c/b\u003e = I am familiar/comfortable with this now (present state)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eGet used to\u003c/b\u003e = The process of becoming familiar/comfortable (action/change)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eBe used to\u003c/b\u003e describes your current state - you are comfortable with something.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eGet used to\u003c/b\u003e describes the process of adapting - you are becoming comfortable with something.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBoth are followed by a \u003cb\u003enoun\u003c/b\u003e or \u003cb\u003everb + ing\u003c/b\u003e, never the infinitive.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Be used to + noun/verb-ing | Get used to + noun/verb-ing",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "are used to working",
                "sentence": "Scientists are used to working long hours in genetic laboratories.",
                "translation_ar": "العلماء متعودون على العمل لساعات طويلة في مختبرات الوراثة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "get used to",
                "sentence": "It took months for researchers to get used to the new DNA sequencing equipment.",
                "translation_ar": "استغرق الأمر شهوراً ليتعود الباحثون على معدات تسلسل الحمض النووي الجديدة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "are used to explaining",
                "sentence": "Genetic counselors are used to explaining complex hereditary conditions to families.",
                "translation_ar": "مستشارو الوراثة متعودون على شرح الحالات الوراثية المعقدة للعائلات"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I'm used to working in the lab",
                "explanation_ar": "بعد used to نستخدم الفعل + ing وليس المصدر",
                "wrong": "I'm used to work in the lab"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She's getting used to studying genetics",
                "explanation_ar": "get used to يحتاج زمن مستمر للعملية الجارية",
                "wrong": "She gets used to study genetics"
              },
              {
                "correct": "We are used to DNA testing",
                "explanation_ar": "نقول are used to وليس are use to",
                "wrong": "We are use to DNA testing"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "b19e8926-f05f-420d-bd7d-709c5a09696d",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Genetic Science",
      "topic_name_ar": "get used to/be used to",
      "topic_name_en": "get used to/be used to",
      "unit_id": "67005d93-4749-4e75-944a-54f88fdf6d5e",
      "unit_number": 9
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "both = كلاهما (إيجابي)، either = أي منهما (اختيار)، neither = لا هذا ولا ذاك (نفي). استخدم فعل مفرد مع either/neither، وفعل جمع مع both",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eBoth\u003c/b\u003e, \u003cb\u003eeither\u003c/b\u003e, and \u003cb\u003eneither\u003c/b\u003e are used to talk about two things or people.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eBOTH\u003c/b\u003e = means 'the two' or 'this one AND that one' (positive)\u003cbr\u003e• Both rooftop gardens and vertical farms are popular in cities.\u003cbr\u003e• Both types of urban farming save space.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eEITHER\u003c/b\u003e = means 'one OR the other' (choice between two)\u003cbr\u003e• You can grow either tomatoes or lettuce in this container.\u003cbr\u003e• Either method works well for beginners.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eNEITHER\u003c/b\u003e = means 'not this one AND not that one' (negative)\u003cbr\u003e• Neither traditional farming nor urban farming is easy.\u003cbr\u003e• Neither of these plants needs much water.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Both + noun/pronoun + plural verb\u003cbr\u003eEither + noun/pronoun + singular verb\u003cbr\u003eNeither + noun/pronoun + singular verb",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "Both hydroponic systems produce",
                "sentence": "Both hydroponic systems produce fresh vegetables.",
                "translation_ar": "كلا النظامين المائيين ينتجان خضروات طازجة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Either vertical farming or rooftop gardening works",
                "sentence": "Either vertical farming or rooftop gardening works in small spaces.",
                "translation_ar": "إما الزراعة العمودية أو زراعة الأسطح تعمل في المساحات الصغيرة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Neither method requires",
                "sentence": "Neither method requires soil.",
                "translation_ar": "لا تتطلب أي من الطريقتين تربة"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Both methods are good",
                "explanation_ar": "both يأخذ اسم جمع وفعل جمع",
                "wrong": "Both method is good"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Either garden is fine",
                "explanation_ar": "either يأخذ اسم مفرد وفعل مفرد",
                "wrong": "Either gardens are fine"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Neither of them is working",
                "explanation_ar": "neither دائماً يأخذ فعل مفرد حتى مع 'of them'",
                "wrong": "Neither of them are working"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Both urban farms",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نحتاج 'of' مع both + اسم مباشر",
                "wrong": "Both of urban farm"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "943aac27-7015-44e2-a948-8f49a3c9294e",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Urban Farming",
      "topic_name_ar": "both/either/neither",
      "topic_name_en": "both/either/neither",
      "unit_id": "99996ac0-6cd8-457d-89ac-e2995c7351e4",
      "unit_number": 10
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم SO مع الصفات والظروف، بينما نستخدم SUCH مع الأسماء. كلاهما يُستخدم للتأكيد وإظهار الدرجة أو الشدة",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eSO/SUCH\u003c/b\u003e are used to emphasize adjectives, adverbs, or nouns to show degree or intensity.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eSO\u003c/b\u003e is used with adjectives and adverbs:\u003cbr\u003e• The data breach was \u003cb\u003eso serious\u003c/b\u003e that many users deleted their accounts.\u003cbr\u003e• She shared her personal information \u003cb\u003eso carelessly\u003c/b\u003e.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eSUCH\u003c/b\u003e is used with nouns (often with adjectives before the noun):\u003cbr\u003e• It was \u003cb\u003esuch a serious privacy violation\u003c/b\u003e that the company was fined.\u003cbr\u003e• They have \u003cb\u003esuch strong passwords\u003c/b\u003e that hackers can't break them.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBoth SO and SUCH can be followed by 'that' to show result or consequence.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "SO + adjective/adverb (+ that + result)\u003cbr\u003eSUCH + (a/an) + (adjective) + noun (+ that + result)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "so much data",
                "sentence": "The app collects so much data that users are worried.",
                "translation_ar": "التطبيق يجمع بيانات كثيرة جداً حتى أن المستخدمين قلقون"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "such a major security flaw",
                "sentence": "It was such a major security flaw that the website was shut down.",
                "translation_ar": "كان عيباً أمنياً كبيراً جداً حتى أنه تم إغلاق الموقع"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "so extensively",
                "sentence": "Social media platforms track users so extensively.",
                "translation_ar": "منصات التواصل الاجتماعي تتبع المستخدمين بشكل واسع جداً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "It was such a big privacy issue",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم SO مع الأسماء - نستخدم SUCH",
                "wrong": "It was so a big privacy issue"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The password is so strong",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم SUCH مع الصفات فقط - نستخدم SO",
                "wrong": "The password is such strong"
              },
              {
                "correct": "So many people worry about privacy",
                "explanation_ar": "مع many و much نستخدم SO وليس SUCH",
                "wrong": "Such many people worry about privacy"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "f14f6548-92f0-41ef-b1b0-b1be140a16cf",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Digital Privacy",
      "topic_name_ar": "so/such",
      "topic_name_en": "so/such",
      "unit_id": "8272e688-818a-4f86-93d5-9a39e84ee3b3",
      "unit_number": 11
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "unless تعني 'إذا لم' أو 'إلا إذا' - شرط سلبي\u003cbr\u003eas long as تعني 'طالما أن' أو 'بشرط أن' - شرط إيجابي\u003cbr\u003eكلاهما يستخدم للحديث عن الشروط والاحتمالات المستقبلية",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eUnless\u003c/b\u003e and \u003cb\u003eas long as\u003c/b\u003e are conditional conjunctions that express different types of conditions.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eUnless\u003c/b\u003e means 'if not' or 'except if'. It introduces a negative condition - something that will happen if the condition is NOT met.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eAs long as\u003c/b\u003e means 'provided that' or 'on the condition that'. It introduces a positive condition - something will happen if the condition IS met.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eBoth are used to talk about future possibilities, requirements, and conditions.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Unless + subject + present tense, subject + will/won't + base verb\u003cbr\u003eAs long as + subject + present tense, subject + will + base verb",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "Unless we solve",
                "sentence": "Unless we solve the radiation problem, astronauts won't survive the journey to Mars.",
                "translation_ar": "إذا لم نحل مشكلة الإشعاع، فلن يتمكن رواد الفضاء من النجاة في الرحلة إلى المريخ"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "As long as the weather conditions are good",
                "sentence": "As long as the weather conditions are good, the Mars rover will continue exploring.",
                "translation_ar": "طالما أن الظروف الجوية جيدة، ستواصل المركبة الفضائية استكشاف المريخ"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "unless NASA receives",
                "sentence": "The mission will fail unless NASA receives additional funding.",
                "translation_ar": "ستفشل المهمة إلا إذا حصلت ناسا على تمويل إضافي"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Unless we prepare properly, the mission will fail.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم will في جملة unless - نستخدم المضارع البسيط",
                "wrong": "Unless we will not prepare properly, the mission will fail."
              },
              {
                "correct": "As long as the fuel lasts, we can reach Mars.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نضع if مع as long as - هذا تكرار",
                "wrong": "As long as if the fuel lasts, we can reach Mars."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Unless you wear a spacesuit, you will die.",
                "explanation_ar": "unless تحتوي على معنى النفي مسبقاً، لا نحتاج don't إضافية",
                "wrong": "Unless you don't wear a spacesuit, you will die."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "c36f5db0-936f-4c5f-87c3-64797960ed2a",
      "level_id": "f7e8dbfb-ec8e-4491-a62d-f54fd4c41aab",
      "level_number": 3,
      "theme_en": "Mars Exploration",
      "topic_name_ar": "unless/as long as",
      "topic_name_en": "unless/as long as",
      "unit_id": "c14c9ffc-13b9-4c4f-9e67-b178f4d85bf6",
      "unit_number": 12
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الشرطية الثالثة تُستخدم للحديث عن مواقف خيالية في الماضي لم تحدث. نستخدمها للتعبير عن الندم أو النقد أو لتخيل كيف كان بإمكان الأمور أن تكون مختلفة.",
            "content_en": "The \u003cb\u003ethird conditional\u003c/b\u003e is used to talk about imaginary situations in the past that didn't happen. We use it to express regret, criticism, or to imagine how things could have been different.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe third conditional describes the result of an unreal past condition. For example, in bioethics, we might discuss what would have happened if different ethical decisions had been made in medical research or patient care.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "If + past perfect, would/could/might + have + past participle",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "had followed... wouldn't have been banned",
                "sentence": "If the researchers had followed proper ethical protocols, the study wouldn't have been banned.",
                "translation_ar": "لو أن الباحثين اتبعوا البروتوكولات الأخلاقية المناسبة، لما تم حظر الدراسة."
              },
              {
                "highlight": "could have lived... had used",
                "sentence": "The patient could have lived longer if the doctors had used gene therapy.",
                "translation_ar": "كان بإمكان المريض أن يعيش فترة أطول لو أن الأطباء استخدموا العلاج الجيني."
              },
              {
                "highlight": "had invested... might have found",
                "sentence": "If we had invested more in stem cell research, we might have found a cure by now.",
                "translation_ar": "لو أننا استثمرنا أكثر في أبحاث الخلايا الجذعية، لربما وجدنا علاجاً بحلول الآن."
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "If I had known about the side effects...",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم 'would' في جملة الشرط، بل نستخدم الماضي التام",
                "wrong": "If I would have known about the side effects..."
              },
              {
                "correct": "If the patient had taken the medicine...",
                "explanation_ar": "نحتاج للتصريف الثالث للفعل مع 'had'",
                "wrong": "If the patient had took the medicine..."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The surgery would have been successful if they had prepared better.",
                "explanation_ar": "النتيجة يجب أن تكون في الماضي أيضاً مع 'have + past participle'",
                "wrong": "The surgery would be successful if they had prepared better."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "8c308e3d-1df1-4adb-9b28-4b8acdd80920",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Bioethics",
      "topic_name_ar": "third conditional",
      "topic_name_en": "third conditional",
      "unit_id": "7fd7a0b6-cbbc-4b38-9cfc-2495554d0f4d",
      "unit_number": 1
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الشرطيات المختلطة تربط بين أزمنة مختلفة: إما شرط في الماضي مع نتيجة في الحاضر، أو شرط عام/حاضر مع نتيجة كان يمكن أن تحدث في الماضي",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eMixed conditionals\u003c/b\u003e combine different time periods to show how a past condition affects the present, or how a present/general condition could have affected the past.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eType 1: Past condition → Present result\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use this when a past action or situation has a result or consequence in the present.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eType 2: Present/General condition → Past result\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use this when a present or general situation could have changed something in the past.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Type 1: If + past perfect, would + base verb\u003cbr\u003eType 2: If + simple past, would have + past participle",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "had discovered → would understand",
                "sentence": "If marine biologists had discovered that deep-sea species earlier, we would understand ocean ecosystems better now.",
                "translation_ar": "لو اكتشف علماء الأحياء البحرية تلك الأنواع في أعماق البحار من قبل، لفهمنا النظم البيئية البحرية بشكل أفضل الآن"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "weren't → would have explored",
                "sentence": "If the ocean weren't so deep, researchers would have explored the Mariana Trench centuries ago.",
                "translation_ar": "لو لم يكن المحيط بهذا العمق، لكان الباحثون استكشفوا خندق ماريانا منذ قرون"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "had been → would have",
                "sentence": "If the deep-sea expedition had been successful, we would have more funding for ocean research today.",
                "translation_ar": "لو نجحت رحلة أعماق البحار، لحصلنا على تمويل أكثر لأبحاث المحيطات اليوم"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "If they had discovered it before, we would know now.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم past perfect في شرط الماضي، وليس simple past",
                "wrong": "If they discovered it before, we would know now."
              },
              {
                "correct": "If the ocean weren't so deep, they would have explored it.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم would have في النتيجة الماضية، وليس will have",
                "wrong": "If the ocean wasn't deep, they will have explored it."
              },
              {
                "correct": "If we had had better equipment, we would find more species now.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تستخدم would في جملة الشرط أبداً",
                "wrong": "If we would have had better equipment, we would find more species now."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "da99c471-d8f5-4d7a-998b-ba64d7246588",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Deep Ocean Discovery",
      "topic_name_ar": "mixed conditionals",
      "topic_name_en": "mixed conditionals",
      "unit_id": "f072a40a-6063-493d-bc9d-4aebe4c472fc",
      "unit_number": 2
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم wish للتعبير عن الندم على الحاضر أو الماضي. الفعل بعد wish يتراجع درجة واحدة في الزمن",
            "content_en": "We use \u003cb\u003e'wish'\u003c/b\u003e to express regret about present situations or past events that we want to be different.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWish + Past Simple\u003c/b\u003e is used for present situations we want to change:\u003cbr\u003e• I wish I had more money to buy organic food. (I don't have enough money now)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWish + Past Perfect\u003c/b\u003e is used for past situations we regret:\u003cbr\u003e• I wish I had planted vegetables last spring. (I didn't plant them, and now I regret it)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe verb after 'wish' goes \u003ci\u003eone step back in time\u003c/i\u003e from the real situation.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Wish + Past Simple (for present regrets) / Wish + Past Perfect (for past regrets)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "wish + grew",
                "sentence": "I wish more people grew their own food.",
                "translation_ar": "أتمنى لو أن المزيد من الناس يزرعون طعامهم"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "wishes + had stored",
                "sentence": "She wishes she had stored more grain before the drought.",
                "translation_ar": "تتمنى لو أنها خزنت المزيد من الحبوب قبل الجفاف"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "wish + provided",
                "sentence": "They wish the government provided better food assistance.",
                "translation_ar": "يتمنون لو أن الحكومة توفر مساعدة غذائية أفضل"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I wish I could afford organic food.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم can بعد wish، بل could",
                "wrong": "I wish I can afford organic food."
              },
              {
                "correct": "I hope I will plant a garden next year.",
                "explanation_ar": "للمستقبل نستخدم hope وليس wish",
                "wrong": "I wish I will plant a garden next year."
              },
              {
                "correct": "I wish I had planted tomatoes.",
                "explanation_ar": "للماضي المنتهي نستخدم had + past participle",
                "wrong": "I wish I have planted tomatoes."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "02c32af7-2410-4e7b-b834-16a9450d3d0e",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Food Security",
      "topic_name_ar": "wish + past/past perfect",
      "topic_name_en": "wish + past/past perfect",
      "unit_id": "f37d15fc-9fed-4c19-a62a-341de2541645",
      "unit_number": 3
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم by للدلالة على الفاعل (من قام بالفعل)، ونستخدم with للدلالة على الأداة أو الطريقة (كيف تم الفعل)",
            "content_en": "In passive voice, we use different prepositions to show the relationship between the action and what performs or accompanies it:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eBY + agent:\u003c/b\u003e Shows WHO or WHAT performs the action\u003cbr\u003e- Velcro was invented \u003cb\u003eby\u003c/b\u003e George de Mestral (person)\u003cbr\u003e- The lotus leaf effect is studied \u003cb\u003eby\u003c/b\u003e scientists (person/group)\u003cbr\u003e- Bird flight patterns are analyzed \u003cb\u003eby\u003c/b\u003e computers (thing that acts)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eWITH + instrument/method:\u003c/b\u003e Shows HOW something is done (the tool, method, or thing used)\u003cbr\u003e- The surface was examined \u003cb\u003ewith\u003c/b\u003e a microscope\u003cbr\u003e- Shark skin texture is replicated \u003cb\u003ewith\u003c/b\u003e 3D printing\u003cbr\u003e- The design was created \u003cb\u003ewith\u003c/b\u003e advanced software\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eNote:\u003c/b\u003e Sometimes both can be used in the same sentence:\u003cbr\u003e- The biomimetic material was developed \u003cb\u003eby\u003c/b\u003e researchers \u003cb\u003ewith\u003c/b\u003e nanotechnology.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + passive verb + by + agent OR Subject + passive verb + with + instrument/method",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "by MIT scientists with nanotechnology",
                "sentence": "Gecko-inspired adhesives were developed by MIT scientists with nanotechnology.",
                "translation_ar": "تم تطوير المواد اللاصقة المستوحاة من الوزغ من قبل علماء معهد MIT باستخدام النانو تكنولوجي"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "by engineers with electron microscopes",
                "sentence": "The butterfly wing structure is being studied by engineers with electron microscopes.",
                "translation_ar": "يتم دراسة تركيب جناح الفراشة من قبل المهندسين باستخدام المجاهر الإلكترونية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "by Olympic committees",
                "sentence": "Shark skin swimsuits were banned by Olympic committees.",
                "translation_ar": "تم منع ملابس السباحة المستوحاة من جلد القرش من قبل اللجان الأولمبية"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "The design was made by the engineer",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم by مع الفاعل وليس with",
                "wrong": "The design was made with the engineer"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The surface was analyzed with a microscope",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم with مع الأدوات وليس by",
                "wrong": "The surface was analyzed by a microscope"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Velcro was invented by George de Mestral",
                "explanation_ar": "الأشخاص يأتون مع by وليس with",
                "wrong": "Velcro was invented with George de Mestral"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "ee2d4bdf-98b0-4064-8ab0-3e8c7e0565fa",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Biomimicry Design",
      "topic_name_ar": "advanced passive (by/with)",
      "topic_name_en": "advanced passive (by/with)",
      "unit_id": "a4d1b754-1a0d-42a5-9ef4-caceaa51ac7d",
      "unit_number": 4
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "نستخدم هذا التركيب عندما نطلب من شخص آخر أن يفعل شيئاً لنا، أو عندما يحدث لنا شيء (غالباً غير متوقع). له استخدامان رئيسيان: الخدمات التي نرتب لها، والأشياء التي تحدث لنا",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eHave Something Done\u003c/b\u003e is used when we arrange for someone else to do something for us, or when something happens to us (often unexpectedly).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eTwo main uses:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. \u003cb\u003eServices we arrange:\u003c/b\u003e When we pay or ask someone to do something for us\u003cbr\u003e2. \u003cb\u003eThings that happen to us:\u003c/b\u003e Often unpleasant experiences\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThis structure is very common when talking about services, repairs, and experiences - including those related to migration and travel.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + have/has/had + object + past participle",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "had her visa renewed",
                "sentence": "Maria had her visa renewed before moving to Canada.",
                "translation_ar": "ماريا جددت تأشيرتها قبل الانتقال إلى كندا"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "having their documents translated",
                "sentence": "The refugees are having their documents translated by volunteers.",
                "translation_ar": "اللاجئون يترجمون وثائقهم من قبل المتطوعين"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "had his passport stolen",
                "sentence": "Ahmed had his passport stolen during his journey to Europe.",
                "translation_ar": "أحمد سُرق جواز سفره أثناء رحلته إلى أوروبا"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I had my car repaired",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نضع الفاعل كمن يقوم بالفعل، بل كمن يطلب الخدمة",
                "wrong": "I had repaired my car"
              },
              {
                "correct": "She has had her hair cut by the hairdresser",
                "explanation_ar": "نحتاج 'had' قبل المفعول والتصريف الثالث",
                "wrong": "She has cut her hair by the hairdresser"
              },
              {
                "correct": "They had their house robbed",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم التصريف الثالث وليس -ing",
                "wrong": "They had their house robbing"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "637eedd5-50e5-4b6a-924f-3194baea2c97",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Human Migration",
      "topic_name_ar": "have something done",
      "topic_name_en": "have something done",
      "unit_id": "9b30bc71-91a8-4316-9166-4319b0589d46",
      "unit_number": 5
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الجمل الوصلية نوعان: محددة (بدون فواصل) وغير محددة (بفواصل). تستخدم للربط وإعطاء معلومات إضافية عن الاسم",
            "content_en": "Relative clauses provide additional information about nouns. There are two main types:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eDefining relative clauses\u003c/b\u003e (essential information - no commas):\u003cbr\u003e- Use: who, that, which, whose, where, when\u003cbr\u003e- Can often omit the relative pronoun when it's the object\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eNon-defining relative clauses\u003c/b\u003e (extra information - use commas):\u003cbr\u003e- Use: who, which, whose, where, when (NOT 'that')\u003cbr\u003e- Cannot omit the relative pronoun\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eAdvanced points:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Prepositions can come before the relative pronoun (formal) or at the end (informal)\u003cbr\u003e• 'What' = 'the thing that/which'\u003cbr\u003e• Reduced relative clauses omit the relative pronoun + be verb",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Noun + relative pronoun (who/which/that/whose/where/when) + clause",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "which was created in 2009",
                "sentence": "Bitcoin, which was created in 2009, revolutionized digital payments.",
                "translation_ar": "البيتكوين، التي تم إنشاؤها في 2009، أحدثت ثورة في المدفوعات الرقمية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "whose portfolio includes Bitcoin",
                "sentence": "The investor whose portfolio includes Bitcoin made huge profits.",
                "translation_ar": "المستثمر الذي تتضمن محفظته البيتكوين حقق أرباحاً هائلة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "What surprised everyone",
                "sentence": "What surprised everyone was the sudden rise in cryptocurrency prices.",
                "translation_ar": "ما فاجأ الجميع هو الارتفاع المفاجئ في أسعار العملات المشفرة"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Bitcoin, which was created in 2009, is popular.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم 'that' في الجمل غير المحددة (التي بها فواصل)",
                "wrong": "Bitcoin, that was created in 2009, is popular."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The wallet, which I bought yesterday, is secure.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نكرر الضمير بعد الضمير الوصلي",
                "wrong": "The wallet, which I bought it yesterday, is secure."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The exchange where I trade is reliable.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نضيف 'there' مع 'where'",
                "wrong": "The exchange where I trade there is reliable."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "31b7c762-fc8f-43ae-a814-74e3464abd19",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Cryptocurrency",
      "topic_name_ar": "relative clauses (advanced)",
      "topic_name_en": "relative clauses (advanced)",
      "unit_id": "bdb9ff2e-ece0-41d2-be44-227a3c3b3786",
      "unit_number": 6
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "جمل الاسم المفعول والفاعل تساعدنا على ربط الأفكار وجعل الكتابة أكثر تطوراً. تستخدم صيغة -ing أو -ed/-en لتحل محل الجمل الوصفية الطويلة أو لإظهار الوقت والسبب والنتيجة",
            "content_en": "Participle clauses help us connect ideas and make our writing more sophisticated. They use the present participle (-ing form) or past participle (-ed/-en form) to replace longer relative clauses or to show time, reason, or result.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003ePresent Participle (-ing):\u003c/b\u003e Shows an action happening at the same time as the main verb, or gives a reason.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003ePast Participle (-ed/-en):\u003c/b\u003e Shows a completed action or passive meaning.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eParticiple clauses can come at the beginning, middle, or end of a sentence. When they come at the beginning, we usually use a comma.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Present participle: [Verb + -ing] + main clause\u003cbr\u003ePast participle: [Past participle] + main clause\u003cbr\u003eOr: Main clause + [participle clause]",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "Feeling anxious in the crowd",
                "sentence": "Feeling anxious in the crowd, Sarah moved toward the exit.",
                "translation_ar": "شعرت سارة بالقلق في الحشد، فتوجهت نحو المخرج"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "influenced by group psychology",
                "sentence": "The protesters, influenced by group psychology, became more aggressive.",
                "translation_ar": "أصبح المتظاهرون، المتأثرون بعلم النفس الجماعي، أكثر عدوانية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Having studied crowd behavior",
                "sentence": "Having studied crowd behavior, the psychologist predicted the riot.",
                "translation_ar": "بعد دراسة سلوك الحشود، تنبأ عالم النفس بالشغب"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Having studied crowd psychology, the expert gave advice.",
                "explanation_ar": "نحتاج 'Having' مع الفعل في الصيغة الثالثة عندما يحدث الفعل قبل الفعل الرئيسي",
                "wrong": "Studied crowd psychology, the expert gave advice."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The crowd, gathering in the square, started chanting.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نحتاج ضمير إضافي بعد جملة الاسم الفاعل",
                "wrong": "The crowd, gathering in the square, they started chanting."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Being excited, the crowd cheered loudly.",
                "explanation_ar": "الفاعل واحد فقط - إما الاسم أو الضمير، وليس الاثنين معاً",
                "wrong": "Being excited, the crowd they cheered loudly."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "75ffd2b0-f1dc-4ec3-834d-3735a4362acc",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Crowd Psychology",
      "topic_name_ar": "participle clauses",
      "topic_name_en": "participle clauses",
      "unit_id": "96004ccc-14a6-4838-9188-08c6445d14c7",
      "unit_number": 7
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "عندما تأتي الظروف السالبة في بداية الجملة للتأكيد، نستخدم القلب (الفعل المساعد قبل الفاعل). هذا يشبه ترتيب الأسئلة في الإنجليزية",
            "content_en": "When certain negative adverbs and adverbial expressions appear at the beginning of a sentence for emphasis, we use \u003cb\u003einversion\u003c/b\u003e (the auxiliary verb comes before the subject, like in questions).\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLook at these examples:\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eNever have forensic scientists solved a case so quickly.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eRarely does DNA evidence lie.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eNot only did the detective find fingerprints, but he also discovered hair samples.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCommon negative adverbs that require inversion: \u003cb\u003enever, rarely, seldom, hardly, scarcely, barely, not only, nowhere, under no circumstances, at no time, only when, only after, only by\u003c/b\u003e.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe inversion follows question word order: \u003cb\u003eNegative adverb + auxiliary verb + subject + main verb\u003c/b\u003e",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Negative adverb + auxiliary verb + subject + main verb",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "Never have I seen",
                "sentence": "Never have I seen such clear fingerprint evidence.",
                "translation_ar": "لم أرَ قط دليل بصمات واضح كهذا"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Rarely does a crime scene reveal",
                "sentence": "Rarely does a crime scene reveal so many clues.",
                "translation_ar": "نادراً ما تكشف مسرح الجريمة عن أدلة كثيرة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Not only did the forensic team find",
                "sentence": "Not only did the forensic team find DNA, but they also recovered the weapon.",
                "translation_ar": "ليس فقط وجد الفريق الجنائي الحمض النووي، بل استعادوا السلاح أيضاً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Never have forensic scientists solved a case so quickly.",
                "explanation_ar": "يجب وضع الفعل المساعد قبل الفاعل",
                "wrong": "Never forensic scientists have solved a case so quickly."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Rarely does DNA evidence lie.",
                "explanation_ar": "نحتاج الفعل المساعد 'does' مع الأفعال في زمن المضارع",
                "wrong": "Rarely DNA evidence lies."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Only when the lab results arrived did we solve the case.",
                "explanation_ar": "القلب يحدث في الجملة الرئيسية، ليس في جملة 'when'",
                "wrong": "Only when the lab results arrived, we solved the case."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "cbf6dc6d-5e35-413b-8d07-7af1b1f612e1",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Forensic Science",
      "topic_name_ar": "inversion after negative adverbs",
      "topic_name_en": "inversion after negative adverbs",
      "unit_id": "b7a132ed-18d7-479b-93ca-e47eefd81b18",
      "unit_number": 8
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الجمل المشقوقة تستخدم للتأكيد على جزء معين من الجملة. نوعان رئيسيان: جمل It-cleft وجمل What-cleft. تستخدم للتركيز على معلومات مهمة أو جديدة",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eCleft sentences\u003c/b\u003e are used to emphasize a particular part of a sentence by splitting it into two clauses. They help us focus attention on specific information.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThere are two main types:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e1. It-cleft sentences:\u003c/b\u003e Start with 'It + be + emphasized part + that/who/which clause'\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e2. What-cleft sentences:\u003c/b\u003e Start with 'What + clause + be + emphasized part'\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use cleft sentences when we want to:\u003cbr\u003e• Emphasize new or important information\u003cbr\u003e• Contrast information\u003cbr\u003e• Answer questions with focus\u003cbr\u003e• Make our speech more dramatic or emphatic",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "It-cleft: It + be + emphasized part + that/who/which + clause\u003cbr\u003eWhat-cleft: What + clause + be + emphasized part",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "It was the archaeologists who",
                "sentence": "It was the archaeologists who discovered the hidden tomb.",
                "translation_ar": "الأثريون هم من اكتشفوا المقبرة المخفية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "What surprised the team was",
                "sentence": "What surprised the team was the perfect preservation of the artifacts.",
                "translation_ar": "ما فاجأ الفريق هو الحفظ المثالي للقطع الأثرية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "It's the mysterious symbols that",
                "sentence": "It's the mysterious symbols that puzzle researchers the most.",
                "translation_ar": "الرموز الغامضة هي التي تحير الباحثين أكثر شيء"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "It was in 1922 that they found Tutankhamun's tomb.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم 'that' وليس 'when' مع الزمن في جمل It-cleft",
                "wrong": "It was in 1922 when they found Tutankhamun's tomb."
              },
              {
                "correct": "What they found was amazing.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نكرر الضمير بعد What-clause",
                "wrong": "What they found it was amazing."
              },
              {
                "correct": "It is the carbon dating that shows the age.",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم 'that' مع الأشياء في معظم الحالات، ليس 'which'",
                "wrong": "It is the carbon dating which shows the age."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "0c1f303a-4d63-4143-a138-50d1be8f5d4f",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Archaeological Mysteries",
      "topic_name_ar": "cleft sentences",
      "topic_name_en": "cleft sentences",
      "unit_id": "b96b7780-37b9-4769-b2c6-65c518515689",
      "unit_number": 9
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "زمن المستقبل التام يصف فعل سيكتمل قبل نقطة محددة في المستقبل. يستخدم مع التعبيرات الزمنية مثل by, before, when. الصيغة ثابتة لجميع الضمائر.",
            "content_en": "The Future Perfect tense describes an action that will be completed before a specific point in the future.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExample sentences:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• By 2050, scientists will have discovered new anti-aging treatments.\u003cbr\u003e• When you turn 80, medical technology will have extended average lifespans significantly.\u003cbr\u003e• Before the end of this decade, researchers will have completed the longevity gene study.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eUse the Future Perfect when:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. An action will be finished before a future time or event\u003cbr\u003e2. To show the order of future events\u003cbr\u003e3. With time expressions like: by, before, when, by the time\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eStructure:\u003c/b\u003e The auxiliary 'will have' stays the same for all subjects, followed by the past participle of the main verb.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + will have + past participle",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "will have found",
                "sentence": "By 2060, scientists will have found a cure for aging.",
                "translation_ar": "بحلول عام 2060، سيكون العلماء قد وجدوا علاجاً للشيخوخة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "will have increased",
                "sentence": "Before you retire, life expectancy will have increased by 20 years.",
                "translation_ar": "قبل أن تتقاعد، سيكون متوسط العمر المتوقع قد ازداد بـ 20 سنة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "will have taken",
                "sentence": "When the study ends, participants will have taken the longevity supplement for 10 years.",
                "translation_ar": "عندما تنتهي الدراسة، سيكون المشاركون قد تناولوا مكمل طول العمر لمدة 10 سنوات"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "By 2050, scientists will have discovered new treatments.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم المستقبل التام وليس المستقبل البسيط مع 'by + زمن محدد'",
                "wrong": "By 2050, scientists will discover new treatments."
              },
              {
                "correct": "When I am 90, medicine will have advanced greatly.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تستخدم 'will' في جملة الوقت بعد 'when'",
                "wrong": "When I will be 90, medicine will have advanced greatly."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Before next year, they will have finished the research.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم التصريف الثالث للفعل وليس المصدر بعد 'will have'",
                "wrong": "Before next year, they will have finish the research."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "8ce700f4-afd3-408d-9bb3-d308ea741573",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Longevity Science",
      "topic_name_ar": "future perfect",
      "topic_name_en": "future perfect",
      "unit_id": "be81143a-e416-4298-91d0-f5f9b4f9786e",
      "unit_number": 10
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "المستقبل المستمر يصف أعمال ستكون جارية في وقت محدد في المستقبل. يؤكد على استمرارية الفعل وليس فقط حدوثه. يستخدم للأعمال المخططة أو المتوقعة في المستقبل.",
            "content_en": "The \u003cb\u003efuture continuous\u003c/b\u003e describes actions that will be in progress at a specific time in the future or during a period in the future.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe use it to:\u003cbr\u003e• Show an ongoing action at a specific future time\u003cbr\u003e• Describe actions that will be happening over a period in the future\u003cbr\u003e• Talk about planned or expected future activities\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe future continuous emphasizes the \u003ci\u003eduration\u003c/i\u003e or \u003ci\u003eongoing nature\u003c/i\u003e of the future action, not just that it will happen.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + will be + verb-ing",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "will be designing",
                "sentence": "Next year, architects will be designing more eco-friendly buildings.",
                "translation_ar": "العام القادم، سيكون المعماريون يصممون مباني أكثر صداقة للبيئة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "will be installing",
                "sentence": "At 3 PM tomorrow, the construction team will be installing solar panels.",
                "translation_ar": "في الساعة الثالثة عصراً غداً، سيكون فريق البناء يركب الألواح الشمسية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "will be becoming",
                "sentence": "By 2030, green buildings will be becoming the standard in architecture.",
                "translation_ar": "بحلول عام 2030، ستكون المباني الخضراء تصبح المعيار في الهندسة المعمارية"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I will be designing sustainable homes next year.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنس 'be' بين 'will' والفعل المنتهي بـ 'ing'",
                "wrong": "I will designing sustainable homes next year."
              },
              {
                "correct": "They will be building green houses tomorrow.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم الفعل مع 'ing' وليس المصدر",
                "wrong": "They will be build green houses tomorrow."
              },
              {
                "correct": "We will be using renewable energy sources.",
                "explanation_ar": "الفعل يجب أن ينتهي بـ 'ing' بعد 'will be'",
                "wrong": "We will be use renewable energy sources."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "86c79213-5784-4c53-9878-1f91b6592754",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
      "theme_en": "Sustainable Architecture",
      "topic_name_ar": "future continuous",
      "topic_name_en": "future continuous",
      "unit_id": "e56f8f63-8f89-4269-b620-b7e2e54f8a8d",
      "unit_number": 11
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الأفعال الناقصة التامة تُستخدم للتعبير عن التكهنات أو الاستنتاجات أو الندم حول أحداث الماضي. must have للاستنتاج القوي، might/could have للإمكانية، should have للالتزام أو النصيحة مع الندم",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eAdvanced Modal Perfects\u003c/b\u003e are used to express assumptions, deductions, or regrets about past actions. They combine modal verbs with perfect infinitives.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eMain uses:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eMust have + past participle:\u003c/b\u003e Strong deduction about the past\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eMight/May/Could have + past participle:\u003c/b\u003e Possibility in the past\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eShould/Ought to have + past participle:\u003c/b\u003e Past obligation or advice (often with regret)\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eWould have + past participle:\u003c/b\u003e Hypothetical past situation\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eCan't/Couldn't have + past participle:\u003c/b\u003e Impossibility in the past\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThese structures help us speculate about past events or express what was possible, necessary, or advisable.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Modal verb + have + past participle",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "must have detected",
                "sentence": "The telescope must have detected the exoplanet's signal last night.",
                "translation_ar": "لابد أن التلسكوب رصد إشارة الكوكب الخارجي الليلة الماضية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "could have discovered",
                "sentence": "Scientists could have discovered this planet years ago with better technology.",
                "translation_ar": "كان بإمكان العلماء اكتشاف هذا الكوكب منذ سنوات بتقنية أفضل"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "should have calibrated",
                "sentence": "We should have calibrated the instruments before starting the observation.",
                "translation_ar": "كان يجب أن نعاير الأجهزة قبل بدء الرصد"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "must have detected",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم have وليس had مع الأفعال الناقصة",
                "wrong": "must had detected"
              },
              {
                "correct": "could have discovered",
                "explanation_ar": "يجب استخدام التصريف الثالث للفعل بعد have",
                "wrong": "could have discover"
              },
              {
                "correct": "should have been",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم have مع جميع الضمائر، وليس has",
                "wrong": "should has been"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "80a7e48e-17cf-4cef-a3bd-615f36f67847",
      "level_id": "81ccd046-361a-42ff-a74c-0966c5293e57",
      "level_number": 4,
