      "topic_name_ar": "advanced modal perfects",
      "topic_name_en": "advanced modal perfects",
      "unit_id": "aceffcb9-98fa-4dd0-9195-f3cd9c59efbc",
      "unit_number": 12
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "صيغة الشك والافتراض تعبر عن المواقف الافتراضية أو المتمنية. تختلف عن صيغة الحقائق وتظهر عدم اليقين أو عدم الواقعية. تستخدم بعد أفعال الطلب والاقتراح والضرورة وفي الجمل الشرطية والأمنيات",
            "content_en": "The subjunctive mood expresses hypothetical, doubtful, or contrary-to-fact situations, wishes, demands, and suggestions. Unlike the indicative mood (stating facts), the subjunctive shows uncertainty or unreality.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe subjunctive appears in:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e1. After verbs of demand/suggestion:\u003c/b\u003e suggest, recommend, insist, demand, require\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e2. After expressions of necessity:\u003c/b\u003e it's essential, it's important, it's vital\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e3. In conditional sentences:\u003c/b\u003e if I were, as if it were\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e4. After wish/regret:\u003c/b\u003e I wish, if only\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIn modern English, the subjunctive is most visible in:\u003cbr\u003e• Third person singular without 's' (He suggest\u003cb\u003es\u003c/b\u003e → that he suggest)\u003cbr\u003e• 'Were' for all persons in hypothetical situations",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Subject + suggest/demand/etc. + that + subject + base verb (no 's') / If + subject + were + ...",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "collapse",
                "sentence": "Historians suggest that the Maya civilization collapse due to environmental factors.",
                "translation_ar": "يقترح المؤرخون أن حضارة المايا انهارت بسبب عوامل بيئية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "were",
                "sentence": "If the Roman Empire were still intact today, our world would be very different.",
                "translation_ar": "لو كانت الإمبراطورية الرومانية ما زالت موجودة اليوم، لكان عالمنا مختلفًا جدًا"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "were",
                "sentence": "I wish ancient civilizations were better documented before their decline.",
                "translation_ar": "أتمنى لو كانت الحضارات القديمة موثقة بشكل أفضل قبل انحدارها"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "I suggest that he go to study archaeology.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نضيف 's' للفعل في صيغة الشك بعد أفعال الاقتراح",
                "wrong": "I suggest that he goes to study archaeology."
              },
              {
                "correct": "If I were living during the fall of Rome...",
                "explanation_ar": "نستخدم 'were' مع جميع الضمائر في الحالات الافتراضية",
                "wrong": "If I was living during the fall of Rome..."
              },
              {
                "correct": "It's important that the civilization survive.",
                "explanation_ar": "الفعل بصيغته الأساسية بعد عبارات الأهمية والضرورة",
                "wrong": "It's important that the civilization survives."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "2922c9d2-88b0-4713-9d39-20380f23bdee",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Civilization Collapse",
      "topic_name_ar": "subjunctive",
      "topic_name_en": "subjunctive",
      "unit_id": "170ce97d-b211-4b25-b19e-fe9fc22fb71b",
      "unit_number": 1
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "التقديم في الإنجليزية يعني نقل عنصر من موضعه الطبيعي إلى بداية الجملة للتأكيد أو التباين. يتطلب عكس ترتيب الفاعل والفعل المساعد مثل الأسئلة. يُستخدم للتعبير عن الإنجازات الاستثنائية والمواقف الدراماتيكية.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eFronting\u003c/b\u003e is an advanced grammatical structure where we move elements from their normal position to the beginning of the sentence for emphasis, contrast, or dramatic effect.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExample sentences:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eNever had she imagined climbing Mount Everest would be so challenging.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eOnly after years of training did he break the world record.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eRarely do we see such extraordinary achievements in sports.\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eFronting is commonly used with:\u003cbr\u003e1. \u003cb\u003eNegative adverbs:\u003c/b\u003e never, rarely, seldom, hardly, barely\u003cbr\u003e2. \u003cb\u003eRestrictive expressions:\u003c/b\u003e only when/after/then, not only...but also\u003cbr\u003e3. \u003cb\u003eConditional structures:\u003c/b\u003e should, were, had\u003cbr\u003e4. \u003cb\u003eEmphasis:\u003c/b\u003e so + adjective, such + noun\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWhen we use fronting, we must \u003cb\u003einvert the subject and auxiliary verb\u003c/b\u003e (like in questions). This creates a more formal, dramatic, or literary tone - perfect for describing extreme achievements and exceptional circumstances.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Fronted Element + Auxiliary Verb + Subject + Main Verb + Rest",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "Never had she imagined",
                "sentence": "Never had she imagined she would win an Olympic gold medal.",
                "translation_ar": "لم تتخيل أبداً أنها ستحصل على ميدالية ذهبية أولمبية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Only after months of preparation did",
                "sentence": "Only after months of preparation did the team reach the summit.",
                "translation_ar": "فقط بعد أشهر من التحضير وصل الفريق إلى القمة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Rarely do athletes achieve",
                "sentence": "Rarely do athletes achieve such remarkable feats.",
                "translation_ar": "نادراً ما يحقق الرياضيون مثل هذه الإنجازات المذهلة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Had I known",
                "sentence": "Had I known the difficulty, I might not have attempted the challenge.",
                "translation_ar": "لو كنت أعرف الصعوبة، ربما لم أكن لأحاول هذا التحدي"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Never had she imagined winning.",
                "explanation_ar": "يجب عكس ترتيب الفاعل والفعل المساعد بعد الظرف المنفي",
                "wrong": "Never she had imagined winning."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Only when he trained hard did he succeed.",
                "explanation_ar": "نحتاج للفعل المساعد did مع الفعل الأساسي بصيغته المجردة",
                "wrong": "Only when he trained hard he succeeded."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Rarely do athletes achieve such success.",
                "explanation_ar": "يجب إضافة الفعل المساعد do/does/did مع التقديم",
                "wrong": "Rarely athletes achieve such success."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Not only did he win the race but also broke the record.",
                "explanation_ar": "التقديم مع not only يتطلب الفعل المساعد وعكس الترتيب",
                "wrong": "Not only he won the race but also broke the record."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "122eb435-2445-4e70-bbd1-71f4433cbf74",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Extreme Achievement",
      "topic_name_ar": "fronting",
      "topic_name_en": "fronting",
      "unit_id": "f14cdead-a656-4d15-9fee-838abb26822b",
      "unit_number": 2
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الحذف في الكلام هو إسقاط كلمات مفهومة من السياق لجعل الكلام أكثر طبيعية وإيجازاً. يشمل حذف الفاعل، الفعل، المفعول، أو جمل كاملة عندما يكون المعنى واضحاً من السياق.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eEllipsis in speech\u003c/b\u003e is the omission of words that are understood from context, making speech more natural and concise. This commonly occurs in informal conversation and dialogue.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eTypes of Ellipsis:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. \u003cb\u003eSubject ellipsis:\u003c/b\u003e Omitting the subject when it's clear from context\u003cbr\u003e2. \u003cb\u003eVerb ellipsis:\u003c/b\u003e Omitting repeated verbs in compound structures\u003cbr\u003e3. \u003cb\u003eComplement ellipsis:\u003c/b\u003e Omitting objects or complements that are understood\u003cbr\u003e4. \u003cb\u003eClause ellipsis:\u003c/b\u003e Omitting entire clauses when the meaning is clear\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eEllipsis makes speech flow naturally and avoids unnecessary repetition, especially in responses, comparisons, and coordinated structures.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Full sentence → Elliptical form (omitting understood elements)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "[I don't believe in alternative medicine]",
                "sentence": "\"Do you believe in alternative medicine?\" \"Not really, no [I don't believe in alternative medicine].\"",
                "translation_ar": "هل تؤمن بالطب البديل؟ - ليس حقاً، لا [أؤمن بالطب البديل]"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "[support]",
                "sentence": "Some scientists support the theory, others [support] opposing views.",
                "translation_ar": "بعض العلماء يدعمون النظرية، وآخرون [يدعمون] وجهات نظر معارضة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "[I have read it]",
                "sentence": "\"Have you read the study on climate change?\" \"Yes, [I have read it] twice.\"",
                "translation_ar": "هل قرأت الدراسة حول تغير المناخ؟ - نعم، [قرأتها] مرتين"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Yes, twice (or) Yes, I have",
                "explanation_ar": "في العربية نحذف أجزاء مختلفة من الجملة، لكن في الإنجليزية يجب الحفاظ على البنية النحوية الصحيحة",
                "wrong": "Yes, I have read twice"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Some believe, some don't",
                "explanation_ar": "يجب استخدام الفعل المساعد المناسب عند الحذف، وليس مجرد 'not'",
                "wrong": "Some believe, some not"
              },
              {
                "correct": "I will go to the conference, she won't",
                "explanation_ar": "تجنب التكرار غير الضروري عند وضوح المعنى من السياق",
                "wrong": "I will go to the conference, she will not go"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "9e2dd537-722e-48c0-a8c1-de5bfeef7aa1",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Scientific Skepticism",
      "topic_name_ar": "ellipsis in speech",
      "topic_name_en": "ellipsis in speech",
      "unit_id": "e707f4f6-1c58-484f-8f94-b1cfe543920e",
      "unit_number": 3
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "التسمية (النومناليزيشن) هي تحويل الأفعال والصفات والجمل إلى أشكال اسمية. هذا يجعل الكتابة أكثر رسمية وأكاديمية، ويساعد في ربط الأفكار بطريقة أكثر سلاسة",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eNominalization\u003c/b\u003e is the process of converting verbs, adjectives, or entire clauses into noun forms. This is a key feature of academic and formal writing, especially in discussing complex topics like climate adaptation.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eNominalization allows us to:\u003cbr\u003e• Create more concise, formal expressions\u003cbr\u003e• Link ideas more smoothly\u003cbr\u003e• Present information objectively\u003cbr\u003e• Build complex arguments efficiently\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThere are several patterns for nominalization:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e1. Verb → Noun:\u003c/b\u003e adapt → adaptation, implement → implementation\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e2. Adjective → Noun:\u003c/b\u003e resilient → resilience, urgent → urgency\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003e3. Clause → Noun phrase:\u003c/b\u003e 'The fact that temperatures are rising' → 'Rising temperatures'",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Verb/Adjective/Clause → Noun/Noun Phrase (using suffixes: -tion, -sion, -ment, -ance, -ence, -ity, -ness)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "implementation",
                "sentence": "The implementation of climate adaptation strategies requires significant investment.",
                "translation_ar": "تنفيذ استراتيجيات التكيف المناخي يتطلب استثماراً كبيراً"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "resilience",
                "sentence": "The resilience of coastal communities depends on early warning systems.",
                "translation_ar": "مرونة المجتمعات الساحلية تعتمد على أنظمة الإنذار المبكر"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Rising sea levels",
                "sentence": "Rising sea levels pose a major threat to island nations.",
                "translation_ar": "ارتفاع مستوى سطح البحر يشكل تهديداً كبيراً للدول الجزرية"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "The construction of sea walls is expensive",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدام الشكل الصحيح للاسم المشتق من الفعل",
                "wrong": "The construct of sea walls is expensive"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Climate vulnerability increases each year",
                "explanation_ar": "تحويل الصفة إلى اسم بإضافة اللاحقة المناسبة",
                "wrong": "Climate vulnerable increases each year"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The reduction of emissions is crucial",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدام الاسم المشتق وليس الفعل في المركب الاسمي",
                "wrong": "The reduce of emissions is crucial"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "7ed5ee81-7d3a-476e-bfca-791a3378783a",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Climate Adaptation",
      "topic_name_ar": "nominalization",
      "topic_name_en": "nominalization",
      "unit_id": "aa881235-3e7b-47d0-b117-eacb0ecf4514",
      "unit_number": 4
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "أدوات الربط المتقدمة تساعد في تنظيم الأفكار المعقدة وإظهار العلاقات المنطقية بين الحجج. تختلف عن أدوات الربط البسيطة وتستخدم في الكتابة الأكاديمية والمهنية لإنشاء نصوص متماسكة ومقنعة.",
            "content_en": "Advanced discourse markers are sophisticated linking words and phrases that help writers and speakers organize complex ideas, show relationships between arguments, and guide readers through detailed discussions. Unlike basic connectors (and, but, so), these markers express nuanced logical relationships and are essential for academic and professional communication.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eTypes of Advanced Discourse Markers:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. \u003cb\u003eContrasting and Conceding:\u003c/b\u003e nevertheless, nonetheless, notwithstanding, be that as it may, granted that\u003cbr\u003e2. \u003cb\u003eAdding and Emphasizing:\u003c/b\u003e furthermore, moreover, what is more, not to mention, above all\u003cbr\u003e3. \u003cb\u003eCause and Effect:\u003c/b\u003e consequently, accordingly, hence, thereby, thus\u003cbr\u003e4. \u003cb\u003eSequencing:\u003c/b\u003e subsequently, henceforth, in the interim, meanwhile\u003cbr\u003e5. \u003cb\u003eSummarizing:\u003c/b\u003e in essence, to sum up, all in all, in the final analysis\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThese markers typically appear at the beginning of sentences or clauses and are followed by commas. They create coherent, sophisticated arguments by explicitly showing how ideas relate to each other.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Sentence 1. + [Advanced Discourse Marker], + [main clause] + supporting information",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "Nevertheless",
                "sentence": "Nuclear power plants generate clean energy. Nevertheless, the issue of radioactive waste disposal remains unresolved.",
                "translation_ar": "محطات الطاقة النووية تولد طاقة نظيفة. ومع ذلك، تبقى مسألة التخلص من النفايات المشعة غير محلولة."
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Furthermore",
                "sentence": "The costs of nuclear energy have decreased significantly. Furthermore, new reactor designs are considerably safer than previous generations.",
                "translation_ar": "انخفضت تكاليف الطاقة النووية بشكل كبير. علاوة على ذلك، التصاميم الجديدة للمفاعلات أكثر أماناً من الأجيال السابقة."
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Consequently",
                "sentence": "Countries are investing heavily in renewable energy sources. Consequently, the demand for nuclear power may decline in the coming decades.",
                "translation_ar": "تستثمر البلدان بكثافة في مصادر الطاقة المتجددة. وبالتالي، قد ينخفض الطلب على الطاقة النووية في العقود القادمة."
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Nuclear energy is controversial. However, many countries rely on it.",
                "explanation_ar": "أدوات الربط المتقدمة عادة تبدأ جملة جديدة وتتبع بفاصلة",
                "wrong": "However nuclear energy is controversial, many countries rely on it."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Nuclear power is clean. Furthermore, it's efficient.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم نقطة قبل أداة الربط المتقدمة، ليس فاصلة",
                "wrong": "Nuclear power is clean, furthermore it's efficient."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Consequently, public opinion changed after the accident.",
                "explanation_ar": "أدوات الربط هذه لا تتبع بحرف جر - تبدأ الجملة مباشرة",
                "wrong": "Consequently of the accident, public opinion changed."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "05bc0c6c-f22e-4ddd-ac8e-2bc8976182c2",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Nuclear Energy Debate",
      "topic_name_ar": "advanced discourse markers",
      "topic_name_en": "advanced discourse markers",
      "unit_id": "d485be14-8f3f-45d2-ba5b-b8853cd3c713",
      "unit_number": 5
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "التحوط (Hedging) يُستخدم لجعل العبارات أقل مباشرة وأكثر مرونة • اللغة الغامضة تجعل العبارات أقل دقة وأكثر عمومية • يُستخدم في السياقات الأكاديمية والرسمية • يُظهر عدم اليقين أو الأدب في التعبير",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eHedging and Vague Language\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eHedging is a technique used to make statements less direct or absolute, showing uncertainty, politeness, or caution. Vague language makes statements less precise, often used in academic and formal contexts.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eExample sentences:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Climate change \u003ci\u003eappears to be\u003c/i\u003e one of the main factors threatening marine biodiversity.\u003cbr\u003e• Deforestation \u003ci\u003etends to\u003c/i\u003e accelerate species extinction rates in tropical regions.\u003cbr\u003e• \u003ci\u003eIt seems that\u003c/i\u003e approximately 1 million species are at risk of extinction.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eFunctions of Hedging:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. \u003cb\u003eSoftening claims:\u003c/b\u003e 'may/might/could' instead of 'will'\u003cbr\u003e2. \u003cb\u003eShowing uncertainty:\u003c/b\u003e 'appears to be', 'seems to', 'suggests that'\u003cbr\u003e3. \u003cb\u003eApproximating:\u003c/b\u003e 'roughly', 'approximately', 'around'\u003cbr\u003e4. \u003cb\u003eGeneralizing:\u003c/b\u003e 'generally', 'typically', 'tend to'\u003cbr\u003e5. \u003cb\u003eLimiting scope:\u003c/b\u003e 'to some extent', 'in many cases', 'largely'\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eCommon Hedging Devices:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Modal verbs: may, might, could, would\u003cbr\u003e• Adverbs: possibly, probably, apparently\u003cbr\u003e• Phrases: it seems that, there is evidence to suggest\u003cbr\u003e• Vague quantifiers: some, several, many, most",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Hedging device + main statement\u003cbr\u003eExamples: Modal + verb | Adverb + statement | It seems/appears + that clause",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "might contribute",
                "sentence": "Pollution might contribute to the decline in bee populations.",
                "translation_ar": "قد يساهم التلوث في انخفاض أعداد النحل"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "appears to be",
                "sentence": "There appears to be a correlation between habitat loss and species extinction.",
                "translation_ar": "يبدو أن هناك علاقة بين فقدان الموائل وانقراض الأنواع"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Roughly 80%",
                "sentence": "Roughly 80% of biodiversity is found in tropical rainforests.",
                "translation_ar": "حوالي 80% من التنوع البيولوجي موجود في الغابات المطيرة الاستوائية"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Scientists suggest that climate change may cause extinction",
                "explanation_ar": "تجنب العبارات القاطعة في السياق الأكاديمي",
                "wrong": "Scientists are certain that climate change causes extinction"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Many species could become extinct",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم كلمات التعميم المرنة بدلاً من الكلمات المطلقة",
                "wrong": "All species will become extinct"
              },
              {
                "correct": "Evidence suggests that deforestation tends to destroy habitats",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم عبارات التحوط للادعاءات العلمية",
                "wrong": "It is proved that deforestation destroys habitats"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "614de71e-ac87-42a3-b91a-c526f5b6cb62",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Biodiversity Crisis",
      "topic_name_ar": "hedging and vague language",
      "topic_name_en": "hedging and vague language",
      "unit_id": "30a2b8b2-b368-4e16-869d-b3a137071340",
      "unit_number": 6
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "التسجيل اللغوي يشير إلى مستوى الرسمية في الاستخدام • الرسمي: جمل معقدة، مصطلحات تقنية، صوت منفعل • غير الرسمي: جمل بسيطة، مفردات يومية، ضمائر شخصية • السياق يحدد الاختيار المناسب",
            "content_en": "Register refers to the level of formality in language use, determined by context, audience, and purpose. In academic and professional contexts like neuroscience research, formal register is essential.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eFormal Register Features:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Complex sentence structures with subordinate clauses\u003cbr\u003e• Passive voice constructions\u003cbr\u003e• Technical vocabulary and precise terminology\u003cbr\u003e• Impersonal tone (avoiding 'I', 'you', 'we')\u003cbr\u003e• Full forms instead of contractions\u003cbr\u003e• Objective language without emotional expressions\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eInformal Register Features:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• Simple, direct sentence structures\u003cbr\u003e• Active voice predominantly\u003cbr\u003e• Everyday vocabulary and colloquialisms\u003cbr\u003e• Personal pronouns and direct address\u003cbr\u003e• Contractions (can't, won't, it's)\u003cbr\u003e• Subjective language with personal opinions\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe choice between formal and informal register affects credibility and appropriateness in professional neuroscience communication.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Formal: Passive constructions + Technical terms + Complex syntax + Impersonal tone\u003cbr\u003eInformal: Active voice + Simple vocabulary + Direct structures + Personal tone",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "were extensively analyzed using",
                "sentence": "The neural pathways were extensively analyzed using advanced neuroimaging techniques.",
                "translation_ar": "تم تحليل المسارات العصبية بشكل مكثف باستخدام تقنيات التصوير العصبي المتقدمة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "We checked out",
                "sentence": "We checked out the brain scans and found some interesting stuff about memory.",
                "translation_ar": "فحصنا صور الدماغ ووجدنا أشياء مثيرة حول الذاكرة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "It is hypothesized that",
                "sentence": "It is hypothesized that synaptic plasticity contributes significantly to cognitive enhancement.",
                "translation_ar": "يُفترض أن المرونة المشبكية تساهم بشكل كبير في تعزيز الإدراك"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Neural mechanisms demonstrate remarkable complexity and adaptability.",
                "explanation_ar": "تجنب الآراء الشخصية والكلمات العاطفية في السياق الأكاديمي",
                "wrong": "I think that neurons are really cool and amazing."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The mechanisms underlying consciousness remain poorly understood.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم البناء للمجهول بدلاً من الاختصارات والتعبيرات العامية",
                "wrong": "Scientists can't figure out how consciousness works."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The findings indicate that memory consolidation is enhanced through repetitive training.",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم مصطلحات دقيقة بدلاً من كلمات بسيطة وعامة",
                "wrong": "The research shows that memory gets better with practice."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "f33b1bf1-e1fe-4709-959e-13df4782337e",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Neuroscience Frontiers",
      "topic_name_ar": "formal vs informal register",
      "topic_name_en": "formal vs informal register",
      "unit_id": "23f63e6e-487f-4588-86de-8a123c5226e9",
      "unit_number": 7
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الكلام المنقول المتقدم يشمل تحويلات معقدة تتجاوز تغيير الأزمنة الأساسية. يركز على نقل الأفكار والتكهنات والتصريحات المعقدة مع الأفعال المساعدة وأفعال النقل المتطورة.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eAdvanced Reported Speech\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eReported speech at C1 level involves complex transformations beyond basic tense changes. We focus on reporting thoughts, speculation, and complex statements with modal verbs, subjunctive-like forms, and sophisticated reporting verbs.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eKey Advanced Patterns:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. \u003cb\u003eReporting thoughts and speculation:\u003c/b\u003e Use verbs like \u003ci\u003esuspect, assume, reckon, figure out\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e2. \u003cb\u003eModal verbs in reported speech:\u003c/b\u003e Complex transformations (might have, should have, etc.)\u003cbr\u003e3. \u003cb\u003eSubjunctive-like reporting:\u003c/b\u003e \u003ci\u003esuggested/insisted/demanded that + subject + base form\u003c/i\u003e\u003cbr\u003e4. \u003cb\u003eReporting questions within statements:\u003c/b\u003e Embedded questions\u003cbr\u003e5. \u003cb\u003eReporting with distancing:\u003c/b\u003e \u003ci\u003eallegedly, supposedly, apparently\u003c/i\u003e",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Complex reporting: Subject + advanced reporting verb + (that) + transformed clause with appropriate modal/tense/subjunctive changes",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "suspected that ant colonies might have developed",
                "sentence": "The researcher suspected that ant colonies might have developed more sophisticated communication systems than previously thought.",
                "translation_ar": "اشتبه الباحث أن مستعمرات النمل ربما طورت أنظمة تواصل أكثر تطوراً مما كان يُعتقد سابقاً"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "insisted that every member study",
                "sentence": "The team leader insisted that every member study swarm behavior patterns before proceeding.",
                "translation_ar": "أصر قائد الفريق على أن يدرس كل عضو أنماط سلوك الأسراب قبل المتابعة"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "wondered how bees could navigate",
                "sentence": "Scientists wondered how bees could navigate so precisely without GPS technology.",
                "translation_ar": "تساءل العلماء كيف يمكن للنحل أن يتنقل بدقة شديدة دون تقنية نظام تحديد المواقع"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "He suggested that she study swarm intelligence.",
                "explanation_ar": "بعد أفعال الاقتراح والإصرار نستخدم المصدر بدون to وليس المضارع المقترن",
                "wrong": "He suggested that she studies swarm intelligence."
              },
              {
                "correct": "They asked how bees communicate.",
                "explanation_ar": "الأسئلة المنقولة تحتاج فعل سؤال مثل asked وليس said",
                "wrong": "They said how do bees communicate."
              },
              {
                "correct": "The expert claimed that ants work together. / Allegedly, ants work together.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم allegedly داخل الجملة المنقولة إذا كان فعل النقل يدل على الادعاء",
                "wrong": "The expert claimed that ants allegedly work together."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "585c5275-104e-41dc-a876-2a77b63ee0ba",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Swarm Intelligence",
      "topic_name_ar": "advanced reported speech",
      "topic_name_en": "advanced reported speech",
      "unit_id": "00ca3625-46ee-4e38-95da-2255f522aff8",
      "unit_number": 8
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "العبارات الاسمية المعقدة تحتوي على عدة مُحدِّدات قبل وبعد الاسم الرئيسي. تتكون من: المُحدِّدات المسبقة (صفات، أسماء فاعل، إلخ) + الاسم الرئيسي + المُحدِّدات اللاحقة (عبارات حرف جر، جمل وصفية، إلخ). مهمة في الكتابة الأكاديمية لضغط المعلومات بكفاءة.",
            "content_en": "Complex noun phrases are extended noun phrases that contain multiple modifiers before and/or after the main noun. They allow us to pack detailed information into a single phrase, making our writing more sophisticated and precise.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eStructure of Complex Noun Phrases:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003ePre-modifiers:\u003c/b\u003e determiners, adjectives, participles, nouns used as adjectives\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eHead noun:\u003c/b\u003e the main noun\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003ePost-modifiers:\u003c/b\u003e prepositional phrases, relative clauses, participles, infinitives\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eComplex noun phrases are essential in academic and professional writing as they help compress information efficiently while maintaining clarity.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Determiner + Pre-modifiers + HEAD NOUN + Post-modifiers",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "The internationally acclaimed contemporary artist living in Paris",
                "sentence": "The internationally acclaimed contemporary artist living in Paris has revolutionized modern sculpture.",
                "translation_ar": "الفنان المعاصر المشهور دولياً والذي يعيش في باريس قد ثوّر النحت الحديث"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Her groundbreaking research into the neural mechanisms underlying creative thinking",
                "sentence": "Her groundbreaking research into the neural mechanisms underlying creative thinking changed neuroscience forever.",
                "translation_ar": "بحثها الرائد في الآليات العصبية التي تكمن وراء التفكير الإبداعي غيّر علم الأعصاب إلى الأبد"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "The brilliant young composer's latest symphony inspired by ancient mythology",
                "sentence": "The brilliant young composer's latest symphony inspired by ancient mythology received standing ovations.",
                "translation_ar": "سيمفونية الموسيقار الشاب اللامع الأخيرة المستوحاة من الأساطير القديمة نالت تصفيقاً حاداً"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "The very talented artist from Italy",
                "explanation_ar": "الظرف 'very' يجب أن يأتي قبل الصفة، ليس بعد الاسم",
                "wrong": "The artist very talented from Italy"
              },
              {
                "correct": "The beautiful painting in the gallery",
                "explanation_ar": "الصفة يجب أن تأتي قبل الاسم في الإنجليزية، عكس العربية",
                "wrong": "The painting beautiful in the gallery"
              },
              {
                "correct": "A creative and intelligent writer's books",
                "explanation_ar": "تجنب التكرار - استخدم الصفات قبل الاسم بدلاً من الجملة الوصفية عند الإمكان",
                "wrong": "A writer who is creative and intelligent his books"
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "0d60721a-6a37-47cb-b97e-21ccd92a62f0",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Creative Genius",
      "topic_name_ar": "complex noun phrases",
      "topic_name_en": "complex noun phrases",
      "unit_id": "b24ae7ba-d335-47ef-a4ac-6dbdf930fdb7",
      "unit_number": 9
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "أدوات الربط المتقدمة تعبر عن علاقات معقدة بين الأفكار. تستخدم في الكتابة الأكاديمية والرسمية لإظهار التناقض، الشرط، السبب والنتيجة، الإضافة، والزمن بطريقة متطورة.",
            "content_en": "\u003cb\u003eAdvanced linking devices\u003c/b\u003e are sophisticated connectors that show complex relationships between ideas in academic and formal writing. They go beyond simple connectors like 'and' or 'but' to express nuanced logical relationships.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cb\u003eCategories of Advanced Linking Devices:\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e1. \u003cb\u003eConcessive links:\u003c/b\u003e Show contrast despite expectations (albeit, notwithstanding, for all that)\u003cbr\u003e2. \u003cb\u003eConditional links:\u003c/b\u003e Express conditions and consequences (provided that, on condition that, supposing)\u003cbr\u003e3. \u003cb\u003eCausal links:\u003c/b\u003e Show cause and effect relationships (inasmuch as, insofar as, by virtue of)\u003cbr\u003e4. \u003cb\u003eAdditive links:\u003c/b\u003e Add information sophisticatedly (furthermore, moreover, not to mention)\u003cbr\u003e5. \u003cb\u003eTemporal links:\u003c/b\u003e Show time relationships (henceforth, heretofore, in the interim)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThese devices typically appear at the beginning of sentences or clauses and require careful punctuation.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "[Advanced linking device] + [complete clause], [main clause] OR [Main clause]; [advanced linking device], [related clause]",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "nevertheless",
                "sentence": "Quantum entanglement defies classical physics; nevertheless, it has been experimentally verified countless times.",
                "translation_ar": "التشابك الكمي يتحدى الفيزياء الكلاسيكية؛ ومع ذلك، تم التحقق منه تجريبياً مرات لا تحصى"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Notwithstanding",
                "sentence": "Notwithstanding the complexity of quantum mechanics, researchers have made remarkable breakthroughs in quantum computing.",
                "translation_ar": "بالرغم من تعقيد ميكانيكا الكم، حقق الباحثون اختراقات رائعة في الحوسبة الكمية"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "provided that",
                "sentence": "Quantum particles behave predictably, provided that we account for probability rather than certainty.",
                "translation_ar": "الجسيمات الكمية تتصرف بشكل متوقع، شريطة أن نأخذ الاحتمال في الاعتبار بدلاً من اليقين"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Although quantum physics is complex, it fascinates scientists. / Quantum physics is complex; nevertheless, it fascinates scientists.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم 'nevertheless' مع 'although' في نفس الجملة - كلاهما يعبر عن التناقض",
                "wrong": "Although quantum physics is complex, nevertheless it fascinates scientists."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Provided that we understand quantum mechanics, we can develop better technology.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نحتاج 'if' مع 'provided that' لأنها تعبر عن الشرط بالفعل",
                "wrong": "Provided that if we understand quantum mechanics, we can develop better technology."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Furthermore, quantum discovery has revolutionized physics. / Moreover, quantum discovery has revolutionized physics.",
                "explanation_ar": "لا نستخدم أداتي إضافة معاً - كلاهما يؤدي نفس الوظيفة",
                "wrong": "Furthermore and moreover, quantum discovery has revolutionized physics."
              }
            ],
            "type": "common_mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      "id": "ba6f0594-af74-454e-99b7-f84b37b76a46",
      "level_id": "1013dc05-72a1-45e9-926e-fbef8669ccee",
      "level_number": 5,
      "theme_en": "Quantum Discovery",
      "topic_name_ar": "advanced linking devices",
      "topic_name_en": "advanced linking devices",
      "unit_id": "2105dec8-575b-4a6a-8456-261b98a9d6c2",
      "unit_number": 10
    },
    {
      "category": "grammar",
      "explanation_content": {
        "sections": [
          {
            "content_ar": "الأسئلة البلاغية لا تتطلب إجابة - تُستخدم لتوضيح نقطة أو خلق تأثير. شائعة في الخطابات والمناقشات والكتابة الإقناعية.",
            "content_en": "Rhetorical questions are questions that don't require an answer - they're used to make a statement, create emphasis, or provoke thought. They're particularly effective in discussions, presentations, and persuasive writing.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eRhetorical questions can:\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eMake a strong point\u003c/b\u003e: \"Isn't cultural diversity our greatest strength?\"\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eShow disbelief or criticism\u003c/b\u003e: \"How can we ignore such rich traditions?\"\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eEngage the audience\u003c/b\u003e: \"What would the world be like without cross-cultural exchange?\"\u003cbr\u003e• \u003cb\u003eIntroduce topics\u003c/b\u003e: \"Why do some cultures value collectivism while others prioritize individualism?\"\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe answer is usually obvious from the context, and the speaker continues without waiting for a response.",
            "type": "explanation"
          },
          {
            "content": "Question word/auxiliary + subject + verb + (object) + ? (no answer expected)",
            "type": "formula"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "highlight": "Isn't it amazing",
                "sentence": "Isn't it amazing how food can bridge cultural gaps?",
                "translation_ar": "أليس من المدهش كيف يمكن للطعام أن يجسر الفجوات الثقافية؟"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "Who doesn't appreciate",
                "sentence": "Who doesn't appreciate learning about different traditions?",
                "translation_ar": "من لا يقدر تعلم التقاليد المختلفة؟"
              },
              {
                "highlight": "How can we claim",
                "sentence": "How can we claim to be global citizens without understanding other cultures?",
                "translation_ar": "كيف يمكننا أن ندعي أننا مواطنون عالميون دون فهم الثقافات الأخرى؟"
              }
            ],
            "type": "examples"
          },
          {
            "items": [
              {
                "correct": "Isn't cultural exchange important? (Continue speaking without waiting)",
                "explanation_ar": "لا تنتظر إجابة للسؤال البلاغي - استمر في الحديث",
                "wrong": "Isn't cultural exchange important? Yes, it is."
              },
              {
                "correct": "Why should we embrace diversity?",
                "explanation_ar": "استخدم ترتيب الكلمات الصحيح في السؤال",
                "wrong": "Why we should embrace diversity?"
